title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown beef and add onion while cooking.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat mixture.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix butter, egg, Parmesan cheese and spices. Toss spaghetti to coat.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Top with meat mix. Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Continue baking until cheese melts. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: sirloin beef tips
directions: In skillet, brown beef in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours or until tender.
Stir occasionally and add water, if needed.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: Brown chicken in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add soup, water and vegetable combo.
Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Blend well.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Mix in zucchini. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This cake does not need frosting; the chocolate chips take care of that.

title: cream cheese onion dip
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl and mix together.

title: coffee liqueur bread pudding(with caramel sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2 quart shallow baking dish.
Set aside.
Toss bread cubes with melted butter, and place half of them in prepared baking dish.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Top with remaining buttered bread cubes.
In a large bowl, whisk eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla, almond extract and salt.
Heat milk and coffee liqueur in a small saucepan, then whisk into egg mixture. Pour mixture over bread.
Press gently, to moisten the bread cubes. Let stand 30 minutes.
Press bread cubes down again.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Sprinkle mixture over pudding.

title: low calorie yogurt(child snack recipe)
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into yogurt (flavor to taste).
Add fresh fruit and mix.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar until sugar is distributed.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar alternately with eggs, nuts, vanilla, coconut and apples.
Mixture is very stiff.
We use a spatula to mix it.

title: corn bisque
directions: Scald corn, milk and onion together.
Mix flour and water; add to soup.
Cook and stir 20 minutes.
Strain.
Mix hot tomatoes with soda and add to soup.
Season to taste and add butter, bit by bit.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda,
salt,
baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs;
add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini
and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients. Stir until moistened.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour. You can ice it with lemon icing or cream cheese icing.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Bring to boil water, dollop of butter and salt.
Add noodles and boil until tender; rinse.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit juice
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor.
Place in freezer until almost frozen.
Blend again and serve.

title: isaiah's milkshake
directions: Put all ingredients together in a blender and mix until smooth and frothy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and make two loaves in a separate loaf pan. Before baking, pour one can tomato juice over loaves.
Wrap one and freeze for later.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Brown ground beef with diced onion.
When done, drain grease. Boil macaroni.
Chop tomatoes (not too fine).
Add tomatoes to ground beef and onion and simmer on low heat.
Add salt, pepper and ketchup to taste.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Drain macaroni and place in a large bowl.
Stir in beef and tomato mixture.
Mix well and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Prepare
bread
crumbs, minced onions and green pepper. About 1 hour before serving, start heating oven to 350°.
With fork, slightly beat eggs.
Lightly mix in chuck, then crumbs, onions and
peppers.
Add
horseradish
and
mix
the
next 4 ingredients.
Combine
lightly but thoroughly.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Shape
into
a
loaf.
Spread
on top 1/2 cup of catsup.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with cole slaw.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops from pepper; remove seeds and membranes.
Combine salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, rice, egg, 3/4 cup soup, onion and ground beef in bowl.
Stir lightly.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Put asparagus pieces and liquid in blender and blend smooth. In saucepan, combine bouillon and boiling water; add asparagus. Add seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Serve hot with a dot of unsalted butter on each cup or soup plate.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Cut one side of peppers; remove seeds.
Stuff peppers with 1/2 of cheese (1/2 pound).
Mix sausage, Bisquick and remaining cheese in bowl.
Form batter around peppers to look like eggs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together soup and sour cream.
Layer hash browns, layer soup and sour cream until it runs out.
Top with cheese.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour water over dates and soda; let cool.
Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and stir.
Add flour and salt.
Mix together with date mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into lined greased 9-inch square pan or 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream if desired.
May be served warm or cold.

title: farmer's pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops and roll in flour. Brown chops in garlic in hot fat over medium heat. Season with salt and pepper. Place sliced potatoes in baking pan; top with pork chops. Separate onion slices into rings and lay over chops. Blend in sour cream and mustard. Pour over top. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Makes 4 servings.

title: kim's cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and Worcestershire until thoroughly blended.
Form mixture into ball or log.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: *Suggested: onions, green peppers, mushrooms and black olives.

title: cloud cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda; add to batter and blend well.
Drop cookies from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: equal yogurt fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and yogurt.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups or 8 servings; contains approximately 100 calories per serving.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil 5 cups water and sugar together; cool.
Boil and cool 2 tea bags in 2 cups water.
Add sugar and water mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients and freeze for 24 hours.
Place 1 or 2 scoops in glass, then fill with sweet or sour soda pop.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and flour together.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Roll into balls and shape into curved shape.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until tan.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: fruit sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and sour cream. Sift and add flour and baking soda.
Fold in walnuts, dates and cherries.
Put in large greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for loaves or 1 hour and 15 minutes for tube.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Put a toothpick in each ball.
Melt in double boiler the chips and wax. Keep hot.
Dip balls in hot chocolate.
Put on waxed paper.

title: sparkle cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Gradually stir into creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients and chill at least 1 hour. Roll on lightly floured pastry cloth, cut and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and salt.
Add milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Insert wooden skewer in one end of each frankfurter.
Coat with additional flour; dip into cornmeal mixture.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients (do not drain salmon), except additional crumbs and butter, mixing
with a fork until blended.
Shape into 9 patties using 1/4 cup each.
Flatten out slightly.
Dip into the additional crumbs.
Preheat frypan and melt butter; add patties. Brown, turning to brown on both sides.
Serve with chili sauce or catsup.
Garnish with parsley.

title: easy blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberries in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine egg, flour and sugar substitute; stir until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over blueberries.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, salt, water and juice.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into hot mixture. Pour into baked pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt oleo; saute onion, celery and bell pepper.
Add beef consomme, steak sauce, water and rice.
Cook covered in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ann's fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 2 hours in tube pans or 45 minutes in regular pans.

title: chocolate amaretto cake
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a large mixing bowl, beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes. Stir in 2 cups of chocolate morsels. Pour into greased and floured 12 c Bundt pan.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak the beans overnight.
Drain and put into a Dutch oven or heavy pot.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except the rice. Simmer 3 hours or until the beans are well done.
Remove the ham hock or ham bone and cut off meat.
Add to the beans.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook bacon and onions together until bacon starts to brown. Add bacon and onions and remaining ingredients to squash. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes more.

title: italian bean 'n sausage stew
directions: Cut sausage into 3/4-inch pieces; remove casing.
Cook in 12-inch skillet over medium-low heat until lightly browned, about 4 minutes.
Add onions and garlic to skillet; cook until sausage is no longer pink, 3 minutes.
Pour off drippings.

title: mexican salad
directions: Add all ingredients and toss.
Add dressing right before serving.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Make a well in center.
Add Parkay and combined pumpkin, egg and water.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, Crisco oil and Mandarin oranges and juice together.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned rock candy
directions: Cook ingredients quickly, without stirring, to 290°.
Add flavored extract and desired food coloring.
Pour quickly into greased square pan.
Chill until firm; turn out of pan and crack into pieces.

title: hot fruit
directions: Mix apple and pineapple juices.
Add brown sugar and ginger. Add fruit; simmer until fruit is tender.
Serve warm.
Do not overcook.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Put all the ingredients in a blender; whip.
Keep in refrigerator.
Great with chips or over Mexican food.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then egg and beer.

title: apple strudel(circa 1950)
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Then cut in butter with two knives.
Beat egg in a cup.
Fill balance of cup with milk.
Make a well in dry ingredients and stir in the liquid ingredients, including the vanilla.
Roll out on floured board to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Top with sliced apples, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and roll up like a jelly roll.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Then reduce heat to 350° for another 45 minutes.
Note:
If dough is too moist, add more flour.

title: quick jalapeno dip
directions: In the container of an electric blender or food processor, combine cream cheese and tomatoes.
Blend until smooth.
Add chilies; blend well.
Serve with vegetables or nacho chips as dippers.

title: pate
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Add gelatin.
Pour thin layer in bottom of mold that has been oiled with olive oil.
Mash together cream cheese and liverwurst.
Add rest of ingredients and add to consomme.
Whip until well blended.
Pour on top of set gelatin mold and refrigerate.
Unmold and serve with Wheat Thins.

title: favorite potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Use any number of potatoes, depending on how many servings are needed.
Do not peel.
Slice potatoes in round, thin slices.
Boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain water and place in oblong baking dish.
Dot generously with butter and sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Bake about 20 minutes or until tender.

title: asparagus and shrimp salad
directions: Cook shrimp; drain.
Peel.
Discard woody base of asparagus and cook in boiling water about 10 minutes until tender.
Cut to bite rings.
Place shrimp, asparagus, onion and parsley in bowl.
Pour fresh herb dressing over.
Cover and chill well, stirring once or twice to coat.
To serve, drain vegetables and toss with tomato slices and pile into lettuce lined mold.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, soda and ginger. Cut in the shortening.
Reserve 1/2 cup to sprinkle on the top. Then add the egg, molasses, vinegar, water, milk and vanilla.
Put into an oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup crumbs on the top. Bake at 375° until it begins to recede from the pan, about 30 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt the Milky Way bars in a double boiler with one stick of butter.
Set the pan aside to cool.
Cream the sugar and the remaining butter together until smooth.
Add the eggs, then dissolve the soda in the buttermilk and add them in.
Sift the flour with the salt and mix it into the batter.
Stir thoroughly. Add the vanilla, nuts and melted candy bars.
Bake the cake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° and test with a toothpick until done.
Frost with Chocolate Nut Icing.

title: pancakes
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks. Add sugar, milk and shortening to yolks.
Add flour.
Fold in whites.
Cook on griddle.

title: ann's ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: dandelion or endive salad
directions: Carefully
wash
and prepare the dandelion as you would lettuce.
Roll
in	a cloth;
pat dry.
Put into a salad bowl; place in
a
warm
place.
Cut
the bacon in small pieces, fry quickly and drop over the dandelion.
Put the butter and cream in a
skillet;
melt
over a slow fire.
Beat eggs.
Add salt, pepper, sugar
and	vinegar;
mix
with a little slightly warm cream mixture.
Pour into a skillet and, under increased heat, stir
until
dressing
becomes
thick like custard.
Take off; pour piping hot over dandelion.
Stir thoroughly.

title: oven fries (low fat; serves 4)
directions: Set oven rack on upper level; preheat to 450°.
Coat a baking sheet lightly with non-stick cooking spray.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges.

title: bread sticks kids love
directions: Mix dough and let rise until double.
Roll out between palms of hands to pencil-size.
Dip in butter or brush with butter.
May be sprinkled with garlic salt.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: soba
directions: In a nonstick large pan (Dutch oven), spray with Pam.
Throw in all the veggies.
Put heat on medium.
Steam fry veggies, tossing now and then.
Sprinkle in garlic salt and pepper.
When veggies are crisp cooked, throw in noodles and stir to unstick noodles. Add sauces and heat through.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press mix into bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Makes one 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: cabbage chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then refrigerate.

title: strawberry cheese wheel
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves, and mix well.
Chill for several hours.
Fashion into the shape of a wheel.
Use a spoon to press a channel into the wheel along the top.
Fill the channel with the strawberry preserves.
Serve the wheel chilled with an assortment of crackers.

title: lemon poke cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Let cool and poke holes in it with a large spoon.
Mix jello and water.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Top with frosting.

title: lasagna dinner
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain.
Boil noodles; drain.
Melt butter and pour in bottom of pan.
Layer noodles, layer of ground beef, a dash of oregano and pour on sauce. Top with cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Cheddar.
Repeat layers and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix Rice-A-Roni as directed.
Boil broccoli until tender. Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Place in oven and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: white northern bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine beef and onion.
Layer in casserole dish: meat mixture, beans and sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Pour tomato soup over and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party snax(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole or mixing bowl, combine cereals, pretzel sticks and peanuts.
In a 1-cup measure or bowl, combine butter, Worcestershire sauce and salts.
Cook, uncovered, 45 seconds or until melted.
Drizzle in fine steam over cereal mixture, stirring to coat evenly.
Cook, uncovered, 8 minutes or until warm, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grilled fish
directions: Using charcoal grill, have a hot fire; using gas grill, grill on high.
On top of grill place aluminum foil.
Spread olive oil on foil; place fish on grill.
Baste top side of fish with mustard.
Cook 5 minutes and turn.
Baste top and cook until fish is opaque and flaky.
Rule of thumb:
For every 1-inch of thickness of chosen fish, cook 10 minutes.

title: oreo dirt cake
directions: Combine butter, cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Next, mix together milk, pudding and Cool Whip; blend well, combine with cream cheese mixture.
In a large, deep pan start with a layer of cookies, then a layer of pudding and end with a layer of cookies on top.

title: quick and easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts; save juice from boiling to cook egg noodles and mushrooms (if desired).
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients along with diced chicken and egg noodles; stir well.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown meat seasoned with oregano and drain.
Add cheese, stirring mixture frequently until melted.
Spread mixture on your favorite bread and toast in oven.

title: honey apple crisp
directions: Spread sliced apples in a shallow baking dish; sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice and pour honey over all.
In a bowl, mix flour, brown sugar and salt and work in the butter as for biscuits, making a crumbly mixture.
Spread these crumbs evenly over the apples.
(Sprinkle with nuts if desired.)
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is crisply browned.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: squash fritters
directions: Cut squash and boil until tender; mash.
Add egg, minced onion and enough bread crumbs to thicken batter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot fat.
Fry golden brown and serve hot.
Yields 6 to 8.

title: blackberry pie
directions: In pie pan (10 1/2-inch size) mix flour, sugar and salt well. Add oil with milk and spread and shape all ingredients in pie pan with hands.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple cloud
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour filling in, then sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
Slice margarine into thin pats.
Place over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Any pie filling flavor will work.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook first three ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes after it comes to a full boil.
Then add next four ingredients and blend well together.
Spoon out on wax paper to dry.

title: taco casserole
directions: In large frypan, brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Add taco seasoning, water and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Crumble taco shells and add to mixture.
Add tomatoes and kidney beans. Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with lettuce, chopped tomatoes and sour cream, if desired.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Melt butter; saute green pepper, onion and celery until soft. Add rice, tomatoes, broth, salt and Tabasco.
Boil and stir well. Add chicken.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until rice has absorbed most of liquid.

title: chocolate crazy cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Add oil, vinegar and cold water. Beat until smooth; pour into pan. Pound on counter to get rid of air bubbles. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: slush punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until dissolves, then add remaining ingredients.
Combine all and freeze.
Serve (melt until slushy). Add equal amount of 7-Up or ginger ale and slush.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies into crumbs.
Mix all other ingredients, then layer Oreos, pudding, Oreos, pudding, etc.
Refrigerate at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: german pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk and salt in blender; blend until fluffy. Tap in flour, a little at a time, until well mixed.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in a 425° oven.
When bubbly, pour in batter.
Immediately return to oven.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: irene's mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and cocoa.
Add mayonnaise, warm water and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in a 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
May be served warm, topped with vanilla ice cream or used with your favorite white minute frosting.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix well softened cheese and dry pudding.
Add pineapple (drained); mix well.
Refrigerate for about 20 minutes, then mold into a ball.
Mold on wax paper.
Pat on crushed nuts.
Serve on cinnamon crisp graham crackers.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup and 1 can of water so soup won't be lumpy.
To this, add uncooked rice, onion soup mix and remainder of water.
Place salt and peppered chicken on top and cook 1 hour, uncovered.

title: mother's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Put in glass loaf pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chopped vegetables until tender.
Drain.
Add cans of soup to vegetables, milk, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into bottom crust in square baking dish.
Place other dough on top and bake at 350° until crust is done.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Arrange in bowl as listed.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Toss before serving.

title: popovers
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased deep muffin tins, 3/4 full.
Bake in 425° oven until golden brown, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in a saucepan for 2 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce, oregano and pepper.
Bring to boiling. Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, until thickened.
Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and egg in blender; whirl until smooth.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients except rice, macaroni and kidney beans and simmer 1 hour.
Add rice, macaroni and beans and simmer another hour.
Use 2 cups beef stock for a richer soup in place of same amount of water.

title: braised cucumber and corn
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, dill and pepper.
Gradually add liquid from corn.
Stir in cucumber. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add corn; heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: instant fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail with the dry jello.
Add Cool Whip, cottage cheese, and then fold in the bananas.
Set in fridge. Ready to serve in 5 min.

title: glazed carrots and bananas
directions: Put carrots and water in large skillet.
Bring to boiling. Cover; reduce heat and boil gently 15 minutes or until tender. Drain carrots and put in bowl.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add sugar, lemon juice and salt; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add carrots and parsley.
Cook, stirring occasionally until carrots are glazed.
Peel bananas, cut into diagonal slices and add to skillet.
Heat.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat the 3 egg whites until stiff and add last.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450 degrees for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 400 degrees and bake for about 50 minutes.
Makes two pies.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and green peppers. Cook vermicelli. Mix all ingredients. If desired, add 3 tablespoons Sauterne wine over top, then add bread crumbs mixed with parsley and melted butter and sprinkle on top. Bake in 13 x 9 baking dish at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: no-fuss lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef in large skillet, stirring to break up into small pieces.
Drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomatoes with liquid; set aside.
Combine Ricotta cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese and basil.
Spread 2 cups sauce over bottom of an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Arrange 3 (4) lasagna noodles in single layer, pressing into sauce.
Spoon Ricotta cheese mixture on top of noodles.
Sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella and top with 2 cups sauce.
Arrange remaining noodles in a single layer, pressing into sauce.
Top with remaining sauce; spread evenly to cover noodles.

title: grandma's egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix together eggs, sugar, salt, and vanilla. Stir well. Blend in milk and food color, brush pie crust with egg white to keep it from getting soggy. Pour custard into pie crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake until golden brown.

title: hot chicken salad(makes 8  servings)
directions: Toss first 9 ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then melt 1 stick butter and toss with almonds and whole corn flakes. Spoon over and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: virginia's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk and butter.
Add vanilla and salt; pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Measure and sift flour.
Resift twice with soda; set aside. Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly, beating constantly to cream well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well and constantly.
Stir in vanilla.
Turn batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Use salt-free shortening to grease pan.
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool on cooling rack 5 minutes.
Turn cake on rack and cool completely.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix with creamed mixture, then add cereal and coconut.
Add nuts and dates.
Form 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly; remove to rack.
Cool completely. Makes 4 dozen.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Stir lightly and drop in muffin tin. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: While pie shells are baking, wash, drain and slice strawberries.
In saucepan, mix together sugar, gelatin, cornstarch and water; bring to boil.
Stir until thickened.
Cool and fill shells with sliced strawberries.
Pour cooled mixture over and refrigerate until set.
At serving time, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add Bisquick last.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Stir and cook over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and stir in a pinch of salt.
Reduce heat and let slowly boil for 5 minutes. Cool.
Refrigerate in glass jar.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in percolator (36 cups).
Put the remaining ingredients in basket.
Brew like coffee.

title: baumkuchen
directions: Oven set to broil.
Soften 1 stick butter.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat on low with 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat until smooth.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 6 x 10-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with water, cinnamon and salt.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil, then simmer until thick.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine 2 tablespoons melted butter or margarine, 1/2 cup crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, egg, corn and broccoli.
Pour in quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining crumbs and margarine or butter; sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: fruit jam
directions: Bring fruit, sugar and juice to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat. Cook until desired thickness (about 20 minutes).
Add pineapple, Jell-O and Kool-Aid.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook 5 minutes. Pour into sterile jars.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: With electric mixer, beat cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake uncovered in an ovenproof dish at 375° for 15 minutes until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and powdered sugar. Add egg and beat well. Add vanilla and almond flavorings.
(Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.) Mix into creamed mixture.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: mom's strawberry cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Add pureed strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (one 13 x 9-inch pan or two round cake pans).
When cool, ice cake with Strawberry Icing.

title: fruit scones
directions: Sift the flour and salt into a mixing bowl, rub in the fat until it is evenly distributed, then stir in the fruit and sugar. Mix in enough milk to make a soft, but not sticky dough and turn it onto a lightly floured working surface.
Roll out the dough to about 1/2-inch thickness, then dip a 2 1/4-inch cutter in extra flour and cut out as many rounds as possible; lay them on a greased baking tray.
Brush the tops of the scones with milk and bake them on the center shelf of a hot oven (425°) for about 10 minutes, until they are golden brown and well risen.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Stir together ingredients.
Dough should be consistency of cookie dough.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thick. Use cinnamon instead of flour to keep from sticking.
Cut shapes with cookie cutter.
Poke hole for hanging.
To dry, lay on waxed paper at room temperature and turn over twice a day for 4 days.
To speed drying, bake on cookie sheet in warm oven for 2 hours.

title: play dough(welcome school's)
directions: Mix in a saucepan the salt, flour and cream of tartar.
Mix in oil and water.
Cook slowly over very low heat, stirring until thick.
Food coloring may be added with liquids or kneaded in after cooking.
Keeps well in tightly covered container.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place shells in baking dish, cheese side up.
Cover shells with sauce.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake for 40 minutes.
tags: frozen Rosetto stuffed shells with Ricotta cheese

title: bean soup
directions: Cook beans and ham together, until beans are tender. Separately, cook carrots, celery, onions and seasoning together and add to ham and beans.
Cook potatoes and drain, reserving broth.
Mash potatoes.
Add reserved broth to ham and beans, and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add mashed potatoes last and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Blend in Cool Whip well.
Layer graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mix. Use layer of crackers, rest of pudding and third layer of crackers.

title: taters italia
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
In large skillet over high heat, combine tomatoes and seasonings until well blended and heat to a full rolling boil.
Pour into casserole and arrange frozen Tater Tots in single layer on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly in center.
Remove from oven and sprinkle on cheese.
Return to oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Let stand for a few minutes. Drop on waxed paper with teaspoon.
Refrigerate to keep.

title: taco ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cook beef until brown. Remove from heat and drain. Stir in seasoning mix, cheese and water; set aside. Unroll crescent dough; separate into triangles. Arrange triangles into a circle on a greased cooking stone with wide sides overlapping in center and points outside. This leaves a 5-inch open center on stone. Scoop meat mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle.
Bring outside points of triangles down over filling and tuck under wide ends at center.

Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cut bell pepper in a zig-zag style. Place pepper in center of ring and fill with salsa. Mound lettuce, tomato, onion and olives on top of ring surrounding bell pepper. Cut ring; serve garnished with sour cream.

title: olive salad
directions: Using a food processor, process anchovies until they form a paste. Add all ingredients to processor and process until thoroughly combined. Chill overnight.

title: roasted peaches with macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain peaches, reserving 1 cup of syrup.
Pour the syrup into a large baking dish that holds the peaches in a single layer,
Crumble the cookies and moisten with rum or syrup.
Fill the cavities of the peach halves with the cookie mixture.
Cover with foil, bake for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with frozen yogurt.

title: bohunk meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients fairly, but lightly.
Make into patties.
Fry at medium heat, until juice runs out clear.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Make the honey-mustard sauce ahead of time as directed below. Keep refrigerated until ready to use. Preheat oven to 400°. To make honey-mustard sauce, combine mustard and honey in a small bowl.
Stir in dill and orange peel. When ready to prepare chicken, line a baking sheet with foil.
Place chicken skin side down on prepared pan and brush sauce on top of chicken; coat well. Turn the chicken over and gently pull back skin and brush meat with sauce.
Pull the skin back over sauce.
Brush skin with remaining sauce and bake until juices run clear when thickest portion of meat is pierced with a knife, about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into rectangle baking dish. Top with following:

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer the following in a glass Pyrex dish:
green peas, onion, crumbled bacon, minced celery, lettuce and mayonnaise.
Top with sliced eggs and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut black-walnut pound cake
directions: Combine 2 cups sugar, salad oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Combine the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add this to the sugar mixture alternately with the buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, coconut and 2 teaspoons extract.
Pour the batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: microwave chocolate pudding cake
directions: Total cooking time: 9 3/4 to 11 3/4 minutes.

title: reese cups
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add confectioners sugar until consistency to form into balls (size of marbles).
Add vanilla mix thoroughly, this is best done by hand.
Mix chocolate and wax in small double broiler.
Dip balls in chocolate using a toothpick.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: sweet potato-banana casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender, mash and set aside.
Combine mashed banana and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Add banana mixture and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 8-inch square casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Uncover, top with marshmallows and bake an additional 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chicken-stuffing bake
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water and butter to boiling.
In a large bowl, pour hot water and butter over stuffing mixture.
Toss to mix well.
Pat 1/2 of stuffing into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: polish eggs
directions: Chop onion and slice sausage.
Saute in large skillet until sausage is evenly browned and onion is glazed.
Place all eggs in large bowl (you don't need all the yolks if you prefer not to) and beat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put eggs in skillet and cook with the sausage and onion until scrambled to your preference. You may use dill to taste (fresh or dried).

title: marinated rump roast
directions: Cleanse roast with white vinegar, either by pouring over roast or by saturating a paper towel with vinegar.
Place roast in large (up to 12 pound) cooking bag.
Pour beef broth over roast.
Add dry soup mix.
Seal and punch 6 holes in top of bag.
Put in refrigerator and let set for 12 hours.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown beef in a skillet over medium heat. Drain. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. Combine eggs, cheeses and seasonings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and allow to soften.
Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Shape into small balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
For a sausage ball with a less smooth appearance but more "sausage taste", use only 2 cups Bisquick.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with no-stick spray.
Mix coconut and pecans together and spread over bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed on box and pour over coconut and nuts.
Cream together, oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake.
Do not spread.
Bake
at 350° 30 to 40 minutes or until cake is done in the middle.
Cake will have a cracked look on top, giving appearance of earthquake.

title: bread-n-butter pickles
directions: Gently stir salt into thinly sliced cucumbers.
Cover with ice cubes.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Add more ice if it melts; drain onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring quickly to a boil; boil 10 minutes.
Add cucumber and onion slices and bring to boiling point.
Pack into hot jars.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath 30 minutes.
Remove jars from canner and complete seals unless closures are self-sealing type.
Makes 8 pints.

title: oriental cole slaw(this recipe makes a lot)
directions: Brown almonds in 375° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Slow Cooker Method: Put frozen meatballs in crockpot. Mix jelly and chili sauce in separate bowl and pour over meatballs evenly. Sprinkle with 2 packs of Splenda or brown sugar. Cover and cook on low for approximately 4 hours (stirring occasionally).

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in oil with onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add chili powder, cumin, paprika, cloves, bay leaf, salt and water. Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook 1/2 hour more.
Add flour and corn meal until thickened.

title: chocolate-oatmeal bars
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add melted butter, then add milk. Cook over low heat until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Add oatmeal and pecans. Put on wax paper to cool, then cut into bars.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey.
May either barbecue or broil.
Place tinfoil on barbecue grill.
Brush chicken with mixture.
Grill for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush other side with mixture.
Continue grilling for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Put cream cheese, milk and butter into saucepan on medium heat until melted.
Add Parmesan cheese, stir with wire whisk. Add garlic powder to taste.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Melt chocolate and butter. Stir in sugar, then slowly add evaporated milk, stirring as it is added.
Blend well and add vanilla. Cook until thick and creamy. As sauce thickens, add a little milk and stir to blend.
Makes 6 to 8 quarts.

title: easy mix cake
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan while the oven heats to 350°, don't let it burn!
Blend brown sugar and applesauce into melted margarine.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cocoa.
Stir into margarine mixture using a fork. Add raisins, nuts and flavorings.
Spread evenly in the pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, removing stems.
Prepare bread crumbs according to instructions on package (use 1/2 package to every 1 package mushrooms).
Drain water from clams and mix with bread crumbs.
When bread crumbs are cool add cheese (1/2 cup to every package bread crumbs).
Stuff mushrooms according to size of mushroom.
Put small amount butter or margarine on top of each mushroom.
Bake until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger with taco seasoning as directed on package. Set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese with sour cream.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with hamburger mix. Put a layer of shredded lettuce on top of burger mix.
Mix tomato with salsa.
Layer over lettuce.
Cover salsa with shredded cheese.
Microwave or place in a 375° oven until cheese melts. Serve at once with nacho chips.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix blueberries and pineapple in a large pan.
Add dry cake mix.
Pour margarine over dry cake mix. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: best ever bread and butter pickles
directions: Stir salt in thinly sliced cucumbers.
Cover with ice cubes. Let stand 2 or 3 hours.
Drain.
Add onions.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bring quickly to a boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Bring to a boiling point.
Pack loosely into hot jars and seal.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool.
Add in pineapple and pie filling.
Pour into a dish.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Beat at medium speed until blended well.
Pour over jello mix and refrigerate until firm.

title: pound cake
directions: Have everything room temperature.
Cream margarine and Crisco, add sugar and cream well, then eggs one at a time.
Then add 1/2 milk.
Add flour, now add other 1/2 of milk.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300° or 325°.

title: shrimp and pasta marinara
directions: In a large pan, heat oil; add onions, garlic, oregano and basil.
Saute for 1 minute.
Add crushed tomatoes and water. Simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Set aside to age or refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, bring sauce to a simmer and add shrimp while pasta cooks.
Do not overcook the shrimp.
Cook until turns opaque.
Divide shrimp up over the pasta.
Spoon sauce over pasta.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.

title: fish stock
directions: Combine all ingredients in a soup kettle, cover and slowly bring to boil skimming as needed. Lower heat and simmer 1 hour. Strain, cool and refrigerate. Stock has a 4-day shelf life, so it's best to freeze unless using immediately.

title: sure fire veggie soup
directions: Better get a big pot, at least 8 quart.
Put the bouillon cubes and butter in 2 quarts water and let the water start heating while you peel the potatoes and clean the carrots.
Add cubed potatoes, sliced carrots, cabbage, celery and diced onion.
Add enough water to cover these vegetables.
Add 3 or 4 good shakes of the garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Boil until the cabbage and potatoes are tender.
Add the corn, beans and tomatoes, packing water and all.
Simmer at a very low boil for about 30 minutes to let the flavors mingle.
Serve with saltine crackers and peanut butter sandwiches.
Serves 8 with leftovers for later.
Any vegetable can be cooked in this soup.

title: beef mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prick bottom and sides of pie shell with fork.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In small skillet, cook ground beef until brown.
Remove and drain excess fat; set aside.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: Lightly spray 9-inch square pan with cooking spray.
Mix gelatin and water in 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwavable bowl. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve completely. Add marshmallows to gelatin.
Microwave 1 minute until almost melted.
Stir until mixture is smooth (creamy layer will float to the top).
Pour into pan.
Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set. Loosen edges using knife dipped in warm water.
Starting at one end, roll up tightly.
With seam side down, cut into 10 to 12 (1/2-inch) slices.
Serve immediately or keep cold until ready to serve.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Add oil and bay leaves. Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomatoes, water, tomato paste, celery, spaghetti mix, salt and garlic to taste and mustard. Bring to a boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into balls.
Dip in sugar and bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes; take out of oven and add star; return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.
(I refrigerate my dough balls before baking, this makes cookie crack when adding star.)

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown sausage and mushrooms.
Drain well.
Mix milk and eggs.
Place meat and mushroom mixture in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese and pour egg mixture over all.
Bake for 25 minutes or until light brown on top.

title: meat sauce
directions: Chop onion and cook in oil until tender.
Mix rest of ingredients and cook over low heat 1 hour until thick.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve over cooked noodles, rice or spaghetti.
Beef, Spam or hamburger may be substituted for the pork.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour in medium baking dish.
Mix margarine and crackers.
Sprinkle over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Boil sugar and cream to soft ball stage. Then beat mixture (use a mixer) until it becomes sugar like. Add nuts. Spoon on wax paper.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients and bake.

title: icebox cake
directions: Arrange a layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Prepare each package of pudding according to directions; set aside.
Top crackers with 1 flavor of pudding.
If using bananas, slice one in 1/2-inch rounds and press into pudding.

Layer more graham crackers and top with second pudding. Repeat arrangement of sliced bananas; top with third pudding. Crush remaining graham crackers; combine with chopped walnuts. Sprinkle over dish.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine cereal, pineapple and juice; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Stir in cereal mixture.
Shape into loaf. Place in greased shallow baking pan or 1 1/2-quart Pyrex loaf dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with mustard sauce. Makes 6 servings.

title: rice salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in
hot water.	Set aside to cool.
Add pineapple to cooled
rice.	Add
Cool
Whip,
nuts and Jell-O. Put in	slightly
buttered dish.
Refrigerate until congealed. Cut in squares and serve.

title: skillet ham and vegetables au gratin
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook ham and onion in oil about 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until onion is tender.
Stir in potatoes, sauce mix from potato mix, hot water and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vegetables. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until potatoes and vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, pepper, basil, celery seed, onion powder, oregano, paprika and salt in bowl.
Dip chicken in evaporated milk and then coat with crumb mixture.
Place in lightly greased shallow roasting pan.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Brush with oil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and add sausage, bacon, corn and peppers.
Add buttermilk to cornbread consistency.
Add cheese. Pour in greased skillet and bake at 400 degrees for 30-45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Cook sugar, butter, syrup and 1 teaspoon salt (unless you've salted the popcorn).
Boil slowly for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove, add soda; stir and pour over popped corn.
Spread on cookie sheet; place in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir it every 15 minutes.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes for 35 minutes; mash with butter.
Beat in the remaining ingredients.
Put half potato mixture in a greased casserole.
Add half pecans, rest of potatoes and then the rest of the pecans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add flour.
Mix in pecans.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gloria's chili con carne
directions: Melt the margarine.
Saute the onion and garlic.
Add the ground beef and saute, stirring until the meat is well done.
Add the next 4 ingredients (tomato soup, kidney beans, chili powder and salt) and cover.
Cook slowly for one hour.
Serve over rice.

title: beef brisket #1
directions: Place brisket in roaster or Dutch oven.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over brisket.
Add water to cover brisket. Bake at 300° to 325° until tender (about 6 hours).

title: boiled cookies(desserts or cookies)
directions: Put sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in pan; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add the rest.
Mix well and drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Place chicken in large saucepan, cover with water.
Boil until chicken is done (15 to 20 minutes).
Take chicken out (reserve broth) and slice into bite-sized chunks.
Return chicken to broth.

title: tuna rice pilaf
directions: Mix rice, eggs, parsley, pepper and onion.
Drain tuna and add to mixture.
Dissolve curry in warmed soup and milk.
Add to first mixture.
Add sherry or lemon juice.
Bake in greased, covered casserole 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini munchies(quiche)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and spread in baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon carrots
directions: Cut up carrots.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Cream together butter, granulated sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Pour ingredients over carrots in dish. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate-filled peanut butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/2 cup butter, eggs and peanut butter. Reserve 1/3 cup of the dough.
Press the rest of the dough into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco adding eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and soda together.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in coconut, nuts and beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased and floured pans.
Use 3 pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salt water until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Melt margarine in small saucepan. Blend in flour; stir until lumps disappear.
Remove from heat and add milk slowly.
Return to heat and bring to boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Mixture needs to be of medium thickness. Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Continue stirring until cheese melts.
In 1-quart casserole dish, blend cheese mix with macaroni. Serve immediately.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Grease cookie sheet, then place wax paper on and then grease paper.
Put mixture on wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Flip on paper towel after baked and roll, then set aside.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Add apples and cinnamon and cook until tender. Pack in sterilized jars and process at 5 pounds pressure in pressure cooker for 10 minutes or in a water bath for 20 minutes.

title: baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 9-inch pie pan.
Cream the cheese and sugar together.
Add vanilla and eggs one at a time. Bake 45 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Keep in airtight container.
It will keep for 6 months.
Add 3 tablespoons of mix to 1 cup hot water for serving.
Recipe makes 17 cups mix. Adjust to your needs.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Beat eggs and Milnot (canned milk); blend.
Work shortening into dry ingredients, then add eggs and milk mixture.
Knead until makes a smooth dough.
Roll out for pies.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir until blended.
Pour into buttered, 8-inch square pan. Cool.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Combine flour and cocoa powder; set aside.
Beat egg whites with mixer; gradually add sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat until medium peaks form.
Fold in dry ingredients until evenly blended. Fold in butter and vanilla.
Pour in ungreased angel food pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: winter vegetables with mustard sauce
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine potatoes, carrots and water; bring to full boil.
Cover; cook over medium heat 8 minutes.
Add Brussels sprouts.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally until vegetables are crisp-tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables.
Toss to coat.
Yields 6 servings.

title: swiss potato soup
directions: In a medium size heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and carrot; saute for about 5 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in milk, broth, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in potato flakes; cook until slightly thickened (about 1 minute).
Add cheese; cook and stir over medium heat until blended.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients adding broccoli last.
Pour into greased baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs, browned in 1/2 stick butter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Flatten cutlets, making incisions on edges to prevent curling. Sprinkle with salt; dredge with flour.
Coat each floured cutlet with egg mixed with milk.
Cover completely with crumbs; shake off excess.
Let breaded cutlets stand until ready to cook, but do not refrigerate or freeze.
Cook just prior to serving.
Heat oil to 350° to keep schnitzels almost floating.
Cook each side until golden brown.
Remove from oil and finish browning in hot butter. Garnish with lemon and parsley.
Makes 2.

title: sour cream banana cake(second place at the fair)
directions: Mix sugar and butter; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well with a mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sour cream, baking soda, bananas and flour.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken for two
directions: Make sauce of first 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken; garnish with mushrooms and green onions.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours. Makes 2 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add and mix well sour cream and seasoning.
Spread in 6 x 8-inch casserole.
Combine sliced green onions, diced tomatoes and picante sauce.
Mix well and pour over first mixture.
Top with grated cheese and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Serve with corn chips.

title: creamy satin pie
directions: Combine chocolate bits, milk, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water until mixture is blended and smooth. Cool slightly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into chocolate mixture, blending thoroughly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving. Serve with spoonful of whipped cream.
Add instant Sanka to whipped cream for flavor, if desired.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Blend this with shortening. In separate bowl, beat 1 egg, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter or oleo. Press into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Thoroughly blend cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 eggs.
Spread over crumbs.
Top with cherry pie filling and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Line loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches, with aluminum foil; grease.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly (leave nuts and fruits whole).
Spread in pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 3/4 hours.
Remove from pan; gently remove aluminum foil.
Cool; wrap and store in cool place.

title: cherry jubilee cake
directions: Warm cream cheese to room temperature.
Mash with fork on a plate until soft.
Add sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
(Does not have to be smooth.)
Cut cake into 3 horizontal layers.
Ice each layer completely with cream cheese mixture.
Put pie filling between layers.
Refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet over medium heat, stirring until no longer pink. Add tomatoes, taco seasoning and corn. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, for 8 minutes. Place tortilla chips on plates; top with lettuce, then beef mixture. Top with olives, onions, sour cream or other topping of your choice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain. Add remaining ingredients (except for crackers) and blend together well. Top with crushed cheese crackers. Dot with butter. Bake in baking dish 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing in a blender.
Spread on tortillas, sprinkle with olives, onions and peppers.
Roll tightly; refrigerate overnight.
Slice rolls and serve with picante sauce for dip.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: sourdough bread #2
directions: Take 1 cup of sourdough starter out of the refrigerator and let it warm up for 24 hours.
Put 1 cup of starter in a large stoneware, glass or stainless steel bowl.
Add 2 cups warm water and blend in the flour.
If mixture appears lumpy or thick, fermentation will smooth it out.
Cover and let stand in a warm spot for at least 12 hours.
If you want a more sour taste, let mixture ferment for 2 or 3 days.
When the mixture is ready, save 1 cup.
This is your starter for the next batch; put it in the refrigerator.
Now go to Sourdough Bread #3.

title: spiced mixed nuts
directions: In a large bowl combine egg white and water.
Add nuts; toss and coat.
Combine sugar and spice; sprinkle over nuts and toss until well coated.
Place nuts in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately transfer nuts to wax paper.
Cool.
Break up large clusters.
Store in covered container.
Yields 6 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute together onion, celery and oleo; drain off oleo.
Heat and mix together chicken and mushroom soup; add cheese to hot soup and let melt.
Combine all ingredients, adding broccoli last. Bake at 350° in 8 x 8-inch baking dish for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring 1 stick oleo, shortening, 1/2 cup peanut butter and hot water to a boil.
In large bowl combine flour, granulated sugar and baking soda.
Pour boiled ingredients over dry and mix.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla, eggs and sour milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Add softened cream cheese.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Add oats and butterscotch morsels.
Mix well.
Spread in greased and floured 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes (depends on oven difference).
Check with toothpick to see if it is done.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Fold in sliced peaches, then fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust and chill thoroughly.
Makes 1 large pie.
Very good!

title: luau ribs
directions: Mix all but ribs.
Rub ribs on both sides with salt and pepper. Place meat side up in foil lined shallow pan.
Bake in hot 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Pour sauce over ribs. Continue baking in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, basting with sauce. Great with Rice Pilaf.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Bring honey to boil; add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Stir in honey and oats.
Cream margarine and sugar until light; add to honey.
Mix flour, 1/2 teaspoon soda, baking powder and salt into bananas and honey mixture.
Pour into 8-inch cake pans and bake at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine; add remaining ingredients and cook on low until cheese is thoroughly melted. (Or heat in slow cooker on low setting for 4 to 5 hours.)

title: creamy herb dressing
directions: Place all ingredients except oil in a blender container. Blend at high speed; reduce to medium speed.
Uncover and pour in the oil in a steady stream.
Turn off blender as soon as oil is incorporated and dressing is thick.
Makes 1 1/2 cups and stores well in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: salted peanut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add buttermilk.
Combine soda, flour and vanilla together; add to creamed mixture.
Grind peanuts.
Add to cake mixture, saving some for topping the frosting.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gloria's buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; put aside.
In big bowl, put shortening, sugar and salt.
Heat milk; add to mixture in bowl. Mix real good; let stand to cool.
Add yeast, egg and half of flour; mix well, then add the rest of the flour.
Form into ball. Let rise to top of bowl; punch down and let rise again.
Make into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add stew meat.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until meat is browned.
Add water, tomatoes, onion soup, pepper, marjoram, thyme and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery.
Cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add corn and green beans.
Recover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes or until beans are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tart cookie dough
directions: Mix together; roll into balls and form in mini muffin pans. Fill with pie filling.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until edges of crust are a golden brown.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Brown sausage, drain and crumble.
Spread over cheese. Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk.
Add dry mustard and pour over sausage and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, dilute soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours until set.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up to bite size the broccoli and red onions.
Stir in raisins and sunflower seeds.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with strawberries. Mix with marshmallow cream.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: salsa
directions: Finely chop onions, garlic, cilantro and jalapeno peppers.
Mix and add the tomatoes, lime juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well until the tomatoes are partially liquefied but still lumpy.

title: barb's french toast
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Add water, apples and cinnamon. Cook apples until tender. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool. Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Place bread over apples.
Pour egg mixture over bread slices.
Cover overnight.
Remove cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover the last 15 minutes if browning too fast.

title: sweet and sour dressing for spinach salad
directions: Process onion in blender until minced.
Add oil, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Process until well mixed.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: french beef stew
directions: Chop vegetables (medium-sized pieces).
Cube beef stew (medium-sized pieces or large, if you so desire).
Mix raw meat, vegetables and tapioca in large bowl.
Put into greased casserole; pour hot bouillon over all.
Add salt and pepper.

title: cheesecake diamonds
directions: Cream vanilla, butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remainder in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: "pan" cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, mix sugar and cocoa.
Stir in water and add marshmallows which have been cut into quarters. Pour cake batter, prepared according to package directions, over mixture in pan.
Top with nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: jacksonville crisp
directions: Cream shortening and gradually add the white and brown sugar. Cream until fluffy.
Add the beaten egg and mix thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into the cream mixture and mix well.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix until well blended.
Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Any cereal may be substituted for the corn flakes and Cheerios are especially good.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Butter pan or casserole dish; crumble bread in bottom of dish. Brown, drain and crumble sausage over bread.
Mix soup and milk and pour over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Delicious for breakfast or any time of the day treat!

title: cocoa cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Remove and pour over dry mixture, beat well.
Add buttermilk, soda, cinnamon, eggs and vanilla. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo and pour into large mixing bowl.
Blend in cocoa, sugar and vanilla; mix well and add eggs, flour, coconut and nuts. Beat 2 minutes and pour into oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and smooth Marshmallow Creme on top while still hot.

title: jalapeno hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add rest of ingredients and stir until blended.
Drop by spoon (whichever size you prefer) into hot deep fat (350°).
Fry each one at least 3 minutes or until brown.

title: stella d'oro anginetti cream puffs
directions: Prepare Anginetti by slicing off tops.
Hold aside.
Drain crushed pineapple, leaving a little juice.
Mix whipped topping and cream cheese together in a bowl about 1 minute at medium speed.
Add crushed pineapple; blend all 3 ingredients for about 1 minute at low speed.
Drop filling by tablespoon onto bottom layers of cookies.
Replace tops.
Refrigerate puffs until ready to serve.
Filling should be enough to fill all or most of the cookies in the package.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Crumble dry cake mix on top of peaches; cover with thin slices of oleo.
Put in oven and bake at 350° until nice and brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly; top with bits of margarine.
Do not stir.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cool, spread Cool Whip over top and serve.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a Ziploc bag. Marinate in refrigerator for at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in square dish.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: delicious jello
directions: Dissolve jello in cup of boiling water.
Add small can of crushed pineapple.
Add frozen fruit and 1 cup of nuts, cut up. Put marshmallows on top.
Refrigerate.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Early on the day of serving: Mix chuck, onion soup mix, egg and bread crumbs in large bowl.
With hands, form into bite-sized meatballs.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and spices.
Add applesauce and baking soda to the mixture. Then add flour, nuts, raisins and salt; mix it all together. Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: fruit torte
directions: Place 1/2-inch slices of pound cake in bottom of 9 x 13-inch container.
Pour peach juice over cake (just enough to make moist).
Layer following ingredients in order given on top of cake:
peaches, congealed Jell-O, pudding, Cool Whip, any kind of fresh fruit (mandarin oranges, kiwi and strawberries are good.) Make 2 rows of each fruit on top of Cool Whip.

title: steak diane
directions: Pound steaks to 1/4-inch thickness and sprinkle with salt and pepper on both sides.
Combine 2 tablespoons butter and mustard in electric skillet and cook over medium heat until sizzling.
Add steaks and shallots and fry one minute on each side, long enough to cook the surface and brown slightly.
Place steaks on warm dinner plates.
To the pan where steaks were cooked, add quickly 1 tablespoon butter, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice and cook over high heat until syrupy.
Stir in parsley, chives or green onions.
Pour over steaks and serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cauliflower polonaise
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender.
Melt margarine.
Stir in crumbs, parsley, egg and celery salt to taste.
Sprinkle over cauliflower and serve.

title: cabbage and beef casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender. Brown meat and pour off excess fat.
Add onion to meat mixture and cook till soft. Mix cabbage, corn and meat mixture together.
Layer this, alternating with cheese.

title: microwave munching peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in microwave glass bowl.
Place in microwave oven and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes. *Add butter and vanilla to hot mixture beating well.
Return to oven and cook 1 to 2 minutes more. Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour quickly onto greased aluminum foil.
Spread thin.
Cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into pieces.
Store in Ziploc bags.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine butter, 4x sugar, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Put aside.

title: fabulous fruit pizza
directions: Cream together shortening, egg and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 15 minutes in a medium size pizza pan.

title: tian of zucchini, tomatoes and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thinly slice zucchini, tomatoes, potatoes and garlic.
Arrange vegetables in a Pam-sprayed baking dish, alternating the slices of vegetables.
Drizzle olive oil over vegetables and sprinkle with seasonings and basil.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: In skillet, melt butter and saute onions until browned.
Add broth and sherry and simmer on low for 2 1/2 hours.
Spoon soup into heatproof mugs; top with toasted bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and top with slice of Swiss cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: rose kennedy's boston cream pie
directions: Sift flour 3 times.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry and fold in 1/2 the quantity of sugar gradually.
Beat egg yolks and liquids and continue to beat until very thick and pale yellow. Beat in remaining sugar.
Combine yolks and whites, folding together until the mixture is blended.
Mix and sift in flour, baking powder and salt, cutting and folding into the egg mixture. Pour into buttered pan.
Bake in moderate slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well. Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well.
In medium bowl, combine flour, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Mix well; shape 1 tablespoonful (use measuring spoon) of dough around each candy kiss.
In small saucepan, combine white baking bar and shortening; cook and stir over low heat until melted.
Drizzle over cookies.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cincinnati chili(serves 4, or 8 over spaghetti.)
directions: In a covered medium (4-quart) saucepan, sweat onions and garlic in oil over medium flame until soft and translucent, about 8 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, lift out the onions and garlic and set aside.

title: slavic tea cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill dough 3 hours, then form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
When cool, lightly coat in bag of confectioners sugar and serve at showers, Christmas, weddings.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add honey.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Combine 3 cups of flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with water.
Beat well.
Dredge raisins, chopped figs and almonds in remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Gently stir into batter.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Spoon batter into pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Glaze if desired.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening until soft and smooth.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until very fluffy, then beat in eggs and jam.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition. Turn into 3 greased layer pans and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes.
Put layers together and spread with Caramel Icing.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Stir constantly. Remove from stove and add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Add vanilla; stir.
Drop on waxed paper and cool.

title: grandma's peanut butter rolls
directions: Place sugar, water and corn syrup in a saucepan over low heat. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook without stirring to 255°. Remove from heat and, while beating constantly, pour in a fine stream into egg whites.
Continue beating until mixture holds shape and loses gloss.
Add vanilla.
Knead in powdered sugar. Roll out on powdered sugar surface.
Spread with peanut butter. Roll into a log and slice in desired size pieces.
Freezes well in airtight container.

title: potato candy
directions: Combine vanilla and potatoes.
Slowly add sugar until it makes a stiff dough.
Take small portions and roll thin on waxed paper. Spread with desired amount of peanut butter.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cool in refrigerator 1 hour.
Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: rosie's cake
directions: Omit water from cake mix.
After cake is baked and cooled, top with Cool Whip.

title: rhea's chicken casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients, leaving 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and sliced almonds.
Place in greased casserole dish and sprinkle crumbs and almonds over the top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Place raisins and water in saucepan; bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool; do not drain.
Mix flour with baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Cream margarine/butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in raisins with liquid and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture, blending thoroughly after each addition.
Drop by tablespoon, about 2 inches apart, on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix together.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in sour cream, baking powder, flour, soda and salt.
Let set overnight to chill in refrigerator.
Do not stir in the morning before baking. Bake at 325° to 350° accordingly for approximately
7 to 10 minutes until done, without browning.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press into dish to make a crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Next, mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, pineapple and Cool Whip; spread over pretzel crust.
Dissolve jello; add frozen strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese layer and put in refrigerator for several hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add your favorite fruit (strawberries, etc.).
Mix with ice cream freezer.

title: apple pie goody
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in 8-inch baking dish.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Melt margarine in frypan and brown ground chuck.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cook egg noodles to package directions.
Drain and mix with sour cream and cottage cheese.
Put half of noodle mixture in a 2 1/2 quart dish.
Cover with half of meat mixture, remaining noodle mixture, then meat mixture.
If desired, cover with Cheddar or Mozzarella cheese, grated.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° or until bubbly.

title: orange slice loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise and eggs.
Cut cabbage coarsely and steam lightly, just until tender in water with a pinch of salt and sugar.
Melt butter in 9 x 11 x 2 baking dish or similar size. Sprinkle 3/4 cup flakes over butter.
Spread cabbage over flakes. Pour mayo mixture over cabbage in dish.
Top with cheese and remaining cup of corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight coleslaw
directions: Combine in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before serving.
