Makes 12 to 18 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in a large plastic container or jar. Mix salt, sugar, celery seed and vinegar well; pour over cucumbers and onions in container.
Store in the refrigerator.
This keeps a long time.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend together margarine and sugar.
Beat egg whites; set aside.
Mix other ingredients; fold in egg whites last.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
(You can also place waxed paper in bottom to avoid sticking.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm. Don't overcook.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: baked spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in water enough to limber it, breaking the lengths into 1/4 size length.
When limber, drain.
Add tomato soup in same pot and mix well.
Chop onions, pepper, celery, olives and, if needed, the pimentos, into small pieces, keeping one oversize piece of celery separate.

title: wings and spaghetti
directions: Coat wings in seasoned flour; brown in hot fat.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; add to browned wings.
Season with salt.
Add mushrooms and liquid.
Cover and simmer until wings are tender and the sauce is slightly thickened.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Arrange on platter or shallow bowl.
Place wings over top.
Add the pan gravy.
Serves 4.

title: s. ray's great potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and slice into casserole dish.
Mix together sour cream, mayo, onion and parsley.
Layer potatoes and mixture, then potatoes and mixture and so on until both are gone. End with sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fried chicken marinated in soy sauce
directions: Marinate chicken in whole bottle of soy sauce for 1 hour.
Roll chicken in flour and fry in cooking oil as you would frying regular chicken.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake.
Ice while warm with powdered sugar frosting.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Place cut up chicken into a baking pan.
Melt butter and place over the chicken.
Pour soy sauce over the chicken.
Place in oven preheated at 350°.
Cook for 1 hour.
Excellent with white rice.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onion and green and red peppers; sprinkle with salt.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger with 1/2 or 1 whole onion as desired or make meat balls.
Set aside.
In blender put in tomatoes.
Add 1/2 to 1 whole package spaghetti sauce mix; blend.
Dump into a crock-pot. Put in blender tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, A.1. sauce, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and Italian seasoning; blend. Dump in crock-pot.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to suit taste. Add meat.
Cook on low setting 5 hours.

title: low-fat banana snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch square pan.
Mix banana, egg substitute, buttermilk, 1/2 cup of brown sugar, applesauce and extracts until blended.
Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder until smooth.
Scrape into baking pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Make small sausage balls and brown.
Remove and cook onions and green peppers in sausage grease.
Mix sausage, onions and peppers to creamed corn and mushroom soup.
Cook noodles and cheese together.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Pour rice (uncooked) into greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Mix cream of mushroom soup and water in a bowl.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour mushroom soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, peaches and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: sister's copper carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and add onion and green pepper.
Make sauce.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan in pan. Mix cooked hamburger, oregano, basil, tomato paste and 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Spoon evenly over top.
Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour in pie pan.
Bake until golden brown and knife comes out clean 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: virginia's baked apples
directions: Boil syrup of first 3 ingredients.
Peel, core and halve apples.
Drop in boiling syrup until tender (few at a time).
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake in moderate oven with remainder of syrup in pan, until done!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer rice in 8 x 8-inch dish, uncooked.
Add chicken, cooked and deboned and cut into bite size pieces.
Spread over rice. Mix soup with pea juice and pour over rice, chicken and peas. Spread 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Add sliced mushrooms, if desired.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes until hot and bubbling. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna bunwiches
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Separate biscuits.
On floured board, roll into 5 x 3-inch ovals.
Spoon mixture into 4 ovals. Top with four of the remaining ovals.
Moisten edges; seal by pressing with fork.
Cut desired shapes from remaining ovals. Place atop; brush with egg.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° over 15 minutes or until browned.

title: appetizer meatballs - venison
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; shape into bite sized meatballs and flour lightly.
In skillet, melt butter and brown meatballs. Remove meatballs.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Add meatballs and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield: 50 meatballs.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Fry dipped breasts in Crisco oil for 3 minutes each side. Place on a cookie sheet.
Spoon tomato sauce or pizza sauce on top.
Spice with oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Place in oven at 350° and bake for 15 minutes.
Put Parmesan cheese on and bake again until cheese is melted.

title: date cookies
directions: Sift white flour; add leavening materials and salt.
Then add whole wheat flour.
Beat the egg and add sour milk and the sugar. Beat until they are well mixed.
Melt the shortening and add to the egg mixture.
Add the white flour, then the graham or whole wheat flour, dates and vanilla.
Beat until all are thoroughly mixed. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased pan; bake in a hot oven about 15 minutes.
Let cookies stand a few minutes after removing them from pan.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Heat butter, marshmallows, cocoa and Coca-Cola together.
Pour over flour mixture, add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Add to batter.
Bake in a long pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Carefully stir in potatoes.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: tuna salad supreme
directions: Shred carrots, chop onions and celery until fine.
Chop pickles coarse.
I use an egg slicer to dice eggs.
Add tuna, stir dry. Add sandwich spread and stir.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing, mixing with each addition until of desired consistency.
Spread on bread of choice, enjoy.
Don't be afraid to adjust the ingredients to suit your own taste.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Pour 1/2 in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels, oleo and milk.
Pour over baked cake.
Add nuts, chocolate chips and remainder of cake mix.
Return to oven for 20 minutes (350°). Return temperature to 325° for additional 10 minutes.
Serve with either whipped cream, Cool Whip or powdered sugar.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, salt, lemon juice and 2 cups cold water in a small saucepan.
Stir until cornstarch is dissolved.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add jello; mix until jello is dissolved.
Add food coloring. Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour the glaze over the berries; let stand 10 minutes.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 or 2 hours.
Top with cream.

title: macaroni-cheese-broccoli
directions: Make box of macaroni and cheese by package directions.
Steam broccoli stems.
When broccoli is done, use spoon and cut broccoli into macaroni and cheese.

title: daddy's hot wings
directions: Clean and wash wings thoroughly. Fry in deep fryer, filled with hot, vegetable oil until brown.
Mix hot sauce and butter in sauce pan and simmer.
After chicken is done and drained, pour hot sauce over wings and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine; combine sugar and peanut butter.
Shape into small
balls; melt chocolate
chips
and
paraffin.
Dip balls; put on wax paper.

title: easy cabbage salad
directions: Combine parsley, chopped onion and cabbage.
Add the dressing and toss.
Garnish with the onion rings.

title: no bake mini cheesecake
directions: Mix cheesecake crumbs, sugar, and butter together. Press onto bottoms of each 12 paper or foil lined muffin cups.

title: rainbow jello cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Prick holes every 1/2 inch.
(A straw works pretty well to do this.)
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour jello mix over cake, making sure it goes in the holes.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend fat and spices in a large bowl.
Add sugar mixture, 1/4 cup at a time, creaming after each addition until fluffy.
Beat eggs until thick; add to sugar mixture, blending thoroughly.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, in 3 additions, to sugar mixture, stirring after each addition until blended.
Chill dough for 5 minutes. Use enough shortening to fill a deep heavy pan 1/2 to 2/3 way full when melted; heat to 370°.
Put dough on lightly floured board and shape into ball.
Roll dough to 1/3-inch thick; cut with floured cutter.
Lift doughnuts with wide spatula and place in heated oil, 3 or 4 in oil at a time MAX.
Cook doughnuts until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on absorbent paper (paper towels).

title: special green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet; drain drippings. Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings.
Crumble bacon and cook onion in reserved drippings.
Add bacon, green beans, Cheez Whiz and mushrooms.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apricot salad
directions: Put ingredients, except Cool Whip, in a pot; stir and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Add the Cool Whip and mix thoroughly. Spread over the layer of set jello.
Garnish with grated Cheddar Cheese.

title: cheesecake tarts(yield: approx. 20 tarts)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: maurice salad(makes 6 servings.)
directions: Combine mayonnaise, pickle juice, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce; stir in eggs, onion and pickle.
Allow to refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Wash and break lettuce into bite-size pieces; chill thoroughly.
At serving time, toss dressing with lettuce and place in salad bowl.
Top with chicken, ham, cheese and tomato wedges and a few slices of hard-cooked eggs.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
(For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup flour.)

title: pina colada bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces; add to milk in bowl and soak. Use hands to crush bread.
Squeeze well; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Grease casserole dish with oleo; pour pudding into dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until very firm.
Serve with whipped cream topping if desired.

title: nancy baker's pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Add sugar to butter and beat until lemon colored.
Add egg yolks, milk and flour alternately.
Add flavoring.
Fold in egg whites just before pouring in greased and floured tube pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown. Serves 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Set in pan filled with 2 inches of water.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan combine chopped broccoli, onion, water, bouillon cubes, thyme and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 15 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
In blender or food processor container, using 1/3 broccoli mixture at a time blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan and set aside.

title: rhubarb butter crunch
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and flour.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Mix brown sugar, oatmeal and flour.
Cut in margarine and Crisco.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: apple casserole
directions: Mix sugar,
flour
and cheese.	Spread over apples in 1 quart casserole
dish.
Pour melted butter over mixture.	Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Great side dish.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Mix altogether and freeze.
Take out of freezer 20 minutes before serving.

title: coffee can ice cream
directions: Place ingredients (except ice and salt) into a 1-pound coffee can, taping the lid.
Then put that can into a 3-pound coffee can around the little can.
Place a layer of ice and a layer of salt until can is full.
Put on lid and roll for about 15 minutes.

title: jamie's strawberry pie
directions: Cut about 3/4 of strawberries in small pieces.
Melt cream cheese in large bowl.
When melted, add rest of ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and arrange strawberry halves on top of pie.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Take glass, oblong casserole dish and put rice and seasoning mix with 2 1/3 cups of hot water and stir well.
Wash chicken pieces and arrange on top of rice mixture; salt and pepper them. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is tender.
When done, mix 3/4 can mushroom soup and 1/2 cup of milk together and spoon over whole dish.
Put back in oven until soup mixture bubbles.
Serves 4.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook meat until no longer red. Rinse and put in pan with potatoes, carrots, onions and onion soup. Add water to cover. Cook until potatoes are tender. Mix cornstarch in cup with water to make thickener. Add to soup until thick. Add water as needed.

title: neiman-marcus poppy seed dressing
directions: Using blender, mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice.
Add oil slowly, mixing constantly until thick.
Stir in poppy seed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Toss 1 cup croutons with the melted oleo and place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix the sour cream and soup.
Mix with vegetables.
Pour over croutons.
Crush 1 cup croutons and sprinkle on top.
Dot with oleo.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until tender-crisp.

title: beef stew
directions: In large plastic food storage bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add beef.
Shake to coat.
In Dutch oven, melt butter. Add onion, garlic, coated beef and any remaining flour mixture. Cook over medium-high heat until beef is browned.
Add potatoes, celery, carrots, water and parsley flakes.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beef is tender.
Add wine and bouquet sauce during last 30 minutes of cooking time.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt, vanilla, milk and egg yolks; beat together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: meatball stew
directions: In a bowl, combine beef, bread crumbs and egg; mix thoroughly. Shape into meatballs.
In skillet, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook meatballs until browned.
Pour off fat.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in peanut butter.
Combine egg and milk.
Stir into peanut butter mixture lightly.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: grandmaw beehan's beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets.
Peel.
Drain and pack in jars.
(Cut large ones to fit jars.)
Bring sugar, vinegar and spice to boil and pour over beets until full.
Heat in boiling water and seal at once.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Mix oil and flour; brown. Add onions, pepper and celery. Cook until soft. Add tomatoes, okra and stock; cook until okra is tender. Add chicken and seasonings; simmer 1/2 hour.

title: baker's clay dough
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix in a bowl.
Knead on a lightly floured surface until smooth.
Shape into a ball and return to bowl.
Cover with damp cloth or paper towel until ready to use.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix meat and cracker crumbs in a large bowl.
In a small bowl combine milk, egg, green chilies, taco sauce and spices.
Mix thoroughly, stir into meat.
Pat meat mixture into a microwave 10-cup baking pan (ring type).
Cover with waxed paper.

title: chicken au gratin
directions: Combine chicken, onion, green pepper, pimento and mayonnaise. Spoon into small shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a saucepan; coot until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cool; cut into pieces.

title: chicken and vegetables
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Fry in oleo until brown on all sides.
Add soup and water, blending until smooth.
When bubbly, add vegetables, heating thoroughly.
Serve over rice or biscuits.

title: damson pie
directions: Wash and strain Damsons.
Beat eggs well.
Add margarine, flour, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean relish
directions: Chop green pepper and onions.
Drain all beans.
Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
The longer it's stored, the better.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Stir Jell-O into boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: regina's taco salad
directions: Pour a handful of Fritos on a plate.
Top with meat mixture; then add cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.
Then pour on taco sauce or picante sauce, for taste.

title: jello punch
directions: Melt Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Serves 50.

title: bisquick muffins
directions: Mix together and put in greased muffin pans. Makes 12 large or 24 small rolls. Bake in hot oven.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix stuffing mix as directed on package.
Saute onions and celery in butter. Fry and drain sausage. Stir in sausage, onion, celery and pecans into stuffing, adding a little more hot water if needed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: squash-carrot casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook squash and onion, uncovered, in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Stir together the cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, carrots and sour cream.
Fold in drained vegetables.
Stir together stuffing mix and butter. Sprinkle 2/3 of stuffing mix into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon vegetable mix atop.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix around edges of dish.
Bake, uncovered, about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Delicious.

title: great as a dip or on burgers
directions: Mix with fork until blended smooth.

title: southern coconut pie
directions: Blend butter, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, syrup and flavorings. Stir well.
Sprinkle coconut over bottom of pie shell.
Pour in the filling.
Bake at 375°
for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oriental soup
directions: In Dutch oven, heat chicken broth and bouillon to boiling.
Add shrimp, pea pods, mushrooms, green onions, parsley, angel hair pasta, garlic and cayenne pepper.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine beef and sausage until smooth.
Add onion, oatmeal, salt and pepper.
Cut in ketchup and egg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Use 1 pound of boneless, skinless chicken for stir-fry.
Cook until tender.
Set aside to cool.
Cook spaghetti.
In a skillet, saute the onion and bell pepper in the margarine.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut crusts off bread and flatten with a rolling pin.
Spread each slice with softened cream cheese.
Roll from corner to corner.
Dip in melted oleo and roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: brown derby's (nelson's)
directions: Mix, adding chicken broth last.
Make thick patties, 1 cup each.
Brown.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in the butter until they are transparent.
Add sugar and sweet basil and stir.
Then add the consomme, broth and sherry.
Simmer slowly, uncovered, on low heat.
Pour in soup bowls (ovenproof), top with croutons and Swiss cheese barely overlapping the top of the bowls.
Place under the broiler for a very short time to melt the cheese.
Serve.

title: corn muffin mix corn bread
directions: Melt butter in large dish.
Beat eggs and add sour cream, corn and sugar.
Then add muffin mix and stir real good.
Pour over melted butter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: powdered sugar nut balls
directions: Cream butter until light. Add powdered sugar and beat until fluffy. Stir in vanilla. Blend sifted flour and salt into creamed mixture. Stir in nuts. Shape into walnut-sized balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes. Remove and roll in powdered sugar while hot. When cooled, roll again in powdered sugar.

title: jack's beef stroganoff
directions: Melt a small amount of shortening in large skillet.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Remove and set aside.
Saute beef in same skillet.
Add onion, soup (mixed with water) and Worcestershire sauce.
Add mushrooms.
Place in covered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours or until meat is tender.
About 15 minutes before serving, add sour cream, mixing well and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Add the sherry and serve piping hot.
Serve over noodles.

title: philadelphia cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water.
Mix cream cheese, milk, celery seed and pepper and stir into drained hot cabbage.

title: shipwreck
directions: Place in casserole in order given (grease lightly).
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°, the first 15 minutes covered.

title: granny cake
directions: Ice cake while still hot.

title: our favorite pickles
directions: To a quart of pickles put in given ingredients.
Fill jar with cold vinegar and shake every little while during the day.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil
Add eggplant cubes and cook few minutes till eggplant begins to soften.
Add remaining ingredients and mix like a meatloaf.
Form into small loaves. Place in 9x13 dish.
cover with tomato sauce.
Bake 350° for 45 mins.
Sprinkle with Provolone or Romano cheese.

title: spinach lasagne i
directions: In skillet heat and soften onions and garlic with oil.
Add Ricotta, eggs, Parmesan cheese and thawed, drained spinach.
Cook on stove until slightly browned.
Prepare sauce.
Prepare noodles per package directions.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.

title: nacho bake
directions: Brown beef & drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Stir in salsa and heat thoroughly.
Pour half of chips in a 9x13 dish.
Spoon meat mixture over chips.
Spread sour cream evenly over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture and top with remaining chips.
Bake at 400 degrees until cheese is completely melted.

title: ribs in sweet 'n sour sauce
directions: Brown ribs in skillet before putting in oven, then pour about half recipe over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Divide in 3 parts.
Roll very thin.
Let stand 20 minutes. Drop in boiling stock.
Turn heat low.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: western dip
directions: Blend with mixer until smooth. Chill. Great on Ritz crackers or for stuffing celery sticks.

title: sauteed chicken breasts with mustard sauce(4 servings)
directions: Pound each chicken breast half between sheets of wax paper until flattened to about 1/4-inch.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: boiled dinner
directions: In a large pot, add water (3/4 full), salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Add Polish sausage.
Cook several minutes, then add cabbage, sliced up.
Let cabbage cook several minutes, then add potatoes.
When potatoes are almost done, add green beans.
Cook until green beans are tender.
Serve it up!

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and peanut butter until combined.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla; beat.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 1/2 of cream cheese mixture into pie shell.
Spread 1/2 cup fudge. Cover with remaining cheese mixture; drizzle top with fudge. Freeze for 6 hours, until firm.
Let stand out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with additional milk.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: juliana soup
directions: Fry bacon in oil.
Blend tomatoes and garlic and add to fried bacon.
Add chicken broth powder.
Add all other ingredients and cover with water.
Cover pot and cook 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: onion-cheese pie(quiche)
directions: Prick crust and bake crust for 5 minutes at 400° first.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix everything except cheese together. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: strawberry tassies
directions: Blend margarine and cream cheese.
Gradually add flour and blend well.
Chill 1 hour.
Pinch off pieces of dough about the size of a nickel and place in miniature muffin tins, molding into shells.
Add small amount of jam to each shell and top with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until shells are light tan color.
Remove and cool on wire rack.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: maple cream fudge
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl; cream until smooth.
Slowly blend in sugar.
Add flavoring and nuts; mix until well blended.
Press into 2 well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Cut in squares.
Top each square with a walnut half if desired.

title: sausage bites
directions: Cook and drain sausages well.
Add margarine, cheese and salts.
Mix well.
Spread on muffins.
Cut each muffin 3 times. Freeze on cookie sheet for 20 to 30 minutes.
Place in Ziploc bag.

title: steak seasoning
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Stick holes in the steaks. Pour ingredients over steaks. Melt some butter and worcestershire sauce, pour these over steaks too. Turn steaks every 5 minutes.

title: lo-cal french fries
directions: Place in a bowl with 1 teaspoon oil.
Mix well.
Bake at 475°, turning once, until done.

title: microwave sweet onion casserole
directions: Combine onions and butter in 2-quart covered dish.
Cook on High power for 10 or 12 minutes or until tender, stirring once halfway through cooking time.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook on High power 30 seconds.
Slowly stir in milk and sour cream. Cook on High power for 4 to 6 minutes or until thickened. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook on Medium power 4 to 6 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: salmon patties
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan; blend in flour, salt, celery salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup milk gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Remove skin and bones from salmon; flake.
Add salmon to milk mixture; blend in lemon juice, parsley and onion.
Spread in a shallow pan; chill. Shape into patties.
Mix egg and 3 tablespoons of milk.
Dip patties into egg mixture; roll in crumbs.
Fry in deep oil for 3 minutes.
Drain.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Lay chicken breasts in pan; cover each with a slice of cheese.
Cover with stuffing.
Combine soup and broth.
Pour over all.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake
as
directed.
Spread
half the batter into a greased 13 x
9-inch
pan.
Bake
or
15 minutes, or until done.
Meanwhile, melt the caramels in the milk.
When cake is done, pour
the
caramel mixture over it.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips
and nuts over the caramel.
Add the remaining cake batter and return to oven until done.

title: easy creamed chicken
directions: Cook peas, chopped onion and diced potato in just enough water to barely cover.
Add cream of chicken soup, poultry seasoning and parsley.
Stir until soup blends, then add chicken.
If too thick, add little water.
If you have leftover chicken gravy, it will add to the taste also.
Serve over rice or toast.

title: black magic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Then add the eggs, oil, buttermilk, vanilla and coffee.
Mix well with beater.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and lightly floured pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Combine these ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour in cupcake cups that are 1/3 full.

title: mexican omelette
directions: Mix egg whites, milk, chives and chili powder.
Pour in omelette pan or griddle.
Heat beans just to warm.
Fill omelette with beans and half the picante sauce.
Top omelette with remainder of picante sauce.

title: baked bean soup
directions: Simmer beans, onions and garlic in water for 30 minutes.
Heat tomatoes and add to beans.
Blend flour, butter and salt and pepper into soup mix until it makes a thin paste.
Add macaroni. Serve piping hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 1972 tampa tribune fruitcake
directions: Chop nuts and fruits into medium-sized pieces.
Dredge with small amount of the flour.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add well-beaten eggs and blend well.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together; fold into egg and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; mix well.
Add fruits and nuts, blending well.
Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Line with heavy brown paper and grease again.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool in pan on cake rack.
Makes 5 pound cake.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and margarine, creaming well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted flour and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in tube pan.

title: toasted bacon nuts
directions: Cut bacon strips in 3 pieces.
Wrap each piece around 2 pecan halves.
Fasten with toothpick.
Toast in moderate oven until bacon is crisp.

title: florida shorty corn
directions: Drain corn. Combine ingredients in mixing bowl. Place in refrigerator overnight. Sprinkle parsley for garnish.

title: fruit pie
directions: Drain fruit well and cut in small pieces.
Mix lemon juice in milk and fold in other ingredients.
Put into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: bran muffins
directions: By hand, mix flour, bran and baking soda.
Melt butter and honey together in separate pan.
Remove from heat and add milk and egg to this mixture.
Pour into dry ingredients and stir by hand. Put in 10 cupcake papers and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 1 teaspoon oil until tender. Drain.
Pat crab meat dry on paper towel.
Put in 10-inch deep pie plate.
Spoon in onion.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender; pour evenly in pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken, celery, parsley, salt and pepper.
Gently fold in the whipped cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice and almonds. Chill well before serving.

title: holiday cranberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix enough water to pineapple syrup to make 2 3/4 cups liquid.
Bring liquid to a boil; pour over jello and dissolve thoroughly.
Add cranberry sauce, breaking up and mixing into jello while still hot.
Allow to cool and become syrupy.
Add crushed pineapple, nuts and marshmallows. Refrigerate and chill several hours.
Keep 1 to 2 weeks if well covered and refrigerated.
Great for Thanksgiving and Christmas dinners.

title: harvest relish
directions: Grind vegetables; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.
Yields 8 pints.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Stir together first 6 ingredients. Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan or baking dish of similar size. Stir together Bisquick, sour cream and milk; pour over chicken mixture. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until topping is golden. Let pie set 10 minutes, then spoon out and enjoy with a tossed salad and crusty bread.

title: eggless, milkless cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Blend sugar and shortening.
Add all other dry ingredients.
Add coffee.
Mix well.
Bake until done.

title: mango nut bread
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and mango pulp.
Slowly add dry ingredients to creamy mixture until smooth.
Beat in eggs and pulp until well blended.
Fold in walnuts or pecans.
Pour into well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to one hour until done.
Cool before slicing.

title: slushy strawberry drink
directions: Wash strawberries and remove stems. Slice and freeze in Ziploc bag.
When ready to use, place strawberries in blender. Add water (a little at a time). Add sugar to taste. Blend until slushy.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until brown.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cookie bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, one egg and melted margarine.
Press mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 15-inch pan.
Then combine powdered sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese, nuts and coconut. Mix well and put this mixture over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: curried orange rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in curry powder and rice.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: jam dandy coffee cake
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in a bowl at once.
Beat 50 strokes with fork.
Pour in a 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle top with brown sugar, nuts and dot with grape jam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add soup, water and salt.
Cook, covered, until tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and onions.
Cook until done.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet or saucepan.
Saute onion in margarine until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook and stir until fairly smooth.

title: blue ribbon bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine together; pat into greased and floured (or sprayed with Pam) 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: unforgettable chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard tips of chicken wings.
Cut wings at joints to form 24 pieces.
Fry wings, a few at a time, in 375° oil for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Transfer wings to a serving dish.

title: banana pudding cake(1 gram of fat)
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or glass casserole dish with a nonfat cooking spray.
Prepare cake using Egg Beaters.
While cake is baking, mix sugar and pineapple in a saucepan; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and prick with a fork.
Pour pineapple mixture over top of cake.
Cool completely.
Prepare instant pudding with skim milk as directed on package.
Spread pudding on top of cooled cake.
Slice bananas and put on top of cake.
Spread whipped cream over bananas and place on top of whipped cream.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: linguini
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain.
Rinse in cool water.
Cut up cucumbers, tomatoes and onions (as many as you want).
Add to noodles.
Pour Italian dressing over the first mixture.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme over top.
Keep in refrigeration until ready to eat.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, soda, baking powder and salt; stir in buttermilk.
Add onion and egg.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil, cook until light brown, drain on paper towels.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup margarine and chips.
Put in buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Top with chips and remaining margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Pick chicken off
bones.
Cook	tomatoes,
okra and bay leaf in chicken broth.
Add salt and pepper.
Add all ingredients (remove bay leaves).
Heat and serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef with onion, about 5 minutes. Drain fat. Stir in tomato sauce, water, chili powder, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes longer. Spread butter on tortillas. Cover and set aside.

title: coconut orange frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl, except coconut.
Beat until smooth (about 2 minutes).
Adjust consistency by adding in small amounts orange juice and powdered sugar.
Fold in coconut. Spread on cold cake.
Makes enough to frost top and sides of a 9-inch layer cake.

title: baked apple dessert
directions: Arrange apples in baking dish with a tight cover.
Mix next 7 ingredients and pour over apples.
Mix together graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over top.
Cover and bake about 40 minutes at 325°.

title: frosting mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well.

title: done buttered rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sour cream; mix, then flour.
Spoon into small muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
They freeze well.

title: cranberry frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9x5x3 loaf pan.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Let stand 15 minutes at room temperature. Slice and place on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 6.
(Very pretty for Christmas or Valentine luncheons!)

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers, remove seed and fiber.
Simmer in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Combine cheese, mayonnaise and soup.
Combine with cooked and drained broccoli. Crumble crackers over top.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: taco chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Pour off oil.
Sprinkle taco seasoning on cooked chicken.
Mix salsa and preserves.
Pour over chicken and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: easy vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Pour it into freezer, add ice and rock salt and freeze.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat well the cream cheese, sugar, egg,
and salt.
Then add Chocolate Chips.
Set aside.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat sugar and eggs; add bread and pineapple.
Put part of the butter in the mixture.
Save enough for the top.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
The top and edges will get brown.
Great with ham or pork or potluck suppers.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in apples, coconut and nuts.
Place in greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french tomato soup(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: In a large kettle, butter-steam carrots and onions, covered, for 15 minutes (without browning) or until tender.
Steam rice and add to vegetables with tomatoes and soda.
Add milk and cream. Reheat, without boiling, and season with salt and pepper.

title: apple salad
directions: Fold cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Add apples and Snickers bars.
Chill.

title: tuna and potatoes
directions: Mix Betty Crocker scalloped potatoes according to package and add drained tuna and peas.
Cook according to package instructions.

title: ricotta cheese
directions: Strain and cool the fresh goat milk to 50° or less.
Pour into clean glass canning jars up to within 1-inch of the tops.
Put the lids and bands on and screw them down tightly.
Place jars in a large kettle that is partly filled with water. Cover and bring the water to a boil.
Let it boil for 1 hour, being careful that it doesn't boil down too far. Cool and store in a dark place.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Do not drain any of juices.
Mix all together.
Put in Dixie cups and freeze.
Thaw slightly before eating.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas. Put 1/2 of mixture in refrigerator.
When firm, spread sour cream on top.
Add remaining mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: kanten(japanese gelatin)
directions: Boil the Kanten in 3 cups of water until it is dissolved.
Put in the sugar and let it come to a boil again before turning off the flame.
Pour into a square pan or dish.
Add the extract and pineapple.
Cool and serve in slices.
This recipe will fill a 10 x 14-inch pan 2 1/2 inches deep.

title: shoo-fly cake(amish)
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, oil and sugar. Reserve 1 cup of the crumbs for the topping. Add to the remaining crumbs the boiling water, molasses and soda.
Mix these ingredients well, then pour the batter into a greased 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the reserved crumbs over the batter, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add all dry ingredients together, add to oil mixture and mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Batter will be very stiff.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Better if sits overnight.
Can be eaten with or without icing.
I use Philly cream cheese frosting.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Prepare in food processor or in blender.
If using blender, grind half of ingredients at a time.

title: hillbilly beans
directions: Fry bacon and hamburger.
Drain well.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham and swiss cheese sandwiches
directions: Blend margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Add ham and cheese.
Spread on bread slices and top with bread slice.
Wrap each sandwich in foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.

title: icebox pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg and mix.
Add evaporated milk.
Drain crushed pineapple and add to mixture (leave a little juice).
Add pecans.
Roll vanilla wafers. Sprinkle a layer of crumbs in a loaf pan.
Add alternately, the pineapple and crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours so it will slice easily.

title: faye's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Set aside.
With pastry cutter, blend shortening and eggs with flour and salt. Add water mixture to form dough.
(More flour may be added if needed.) Let rise until doubled in size.
Shape into loaves or rolls.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cheese and blend with sugar.
Add peanut butter; blend well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust and top with chopped nuts (optional).
Serves 8.

title: autumn vegetable salad(55 calories per serving)
directions: Day before serving:
In medium saucepan, cook rutabaga in 1 inch boiling salted water until tender-crisp; drain.
Place in small bowl.
Pour on 1/3 cup of dressing.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Do not stir any of the ingredients in first step.
Sift cocoa and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk and lay butter or margarine stick on top; do not stir.
Cook on High for 6 minutes. Remove from microwave and stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla flavoring and nuts.
Stir until well mixed; pour into buttered platter. Cool in refrigerator 1 hour.
Cut and serve.

title: blackberry buckle
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cardamon onto wax paper. Beat butter and 3/4 cup sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until smooth and light.
Add milk alternately with flour mixture to the butter and sugar, beating just to mix thoroughly. Spread less than half the batter in a buttered 9 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half the berries.
Spoon remaining batter evenly over the berries; smooth with a spatula.
Sprinkle with remaining berries, then top with the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Cool slightly on wire rack.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: new england squash pie
directions: Beat all ingredients but the crust with beater.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake on bottom shelf at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yield: one pie.

title: basic bread pudding(microwave)
directions: Measure milk into 1 quart measuring cup.
Add butter. Microwave at High 4 minutes until butter is melted and milk is warm.
Rapidly stir in eggs with a fork and mix well.
Pour over bread cubes in dish.
Microwave at Medium 9 to 12 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn after 6 minutes.
When cooked, center may still be slightly soft but it will set up as pudding cools.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Turn down and let simmer until onion, etc. are done.
Add pork and beans and let simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix; set aside.
Mix 1 egg and 2 tablespoons oil with remaining cake mix.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and remaining eggs in a bowl. Add reserved (1 cup) cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Add milk, lemon juice and extract.
Beat at low speed and pour over crust.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 300°.
Top with cherries and refrigerate.

title: fried chicken
directions: Beat the egg and half and half.
In a paper bag, mix the flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in the egg, then place in bag and shake.
Fry chicken in a deep skillet until evenly cooked, approximately 30 minutes.

title: stacy's lasagna
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon basil, garlic salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer together 1 hour.
Cook, drain and rinse noodles.
Combine cottage cheese, rest of basil and Parmesan cheese, beaten egg, salt, pepper and parsley.
Arrange in slightly greased casserole dish layers:
noodles, cheese and meat sauce until all is used.
Add Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is golden brown on top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes on high speed and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: queen of muffins
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Add alternately the flour and milk.
Beat a minute and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 20 muffins.

title: veggie dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, onion, dill, parsley, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: slow cooked pepper steak(crock-pot)
directions: Cut beef in 3 x 1-inch strips.
Brown in oil.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Combine the next seven ingredients; pour over beef. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours or until meat is tender. Add tomatoes and green peppers.
Cook for 1 hour longer.
Combine water and cornstarch to make a paste; stir into liquid.
Cook on high until thickened.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cocoa cappuccino mousse
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk, cocoa, butter and coffee in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter melts and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; cool.
Beat whipping cream in large bowl until stiff.
Gradually fold chocolate mixture into whipped cream.
Spoon into dessert dishes. Refrigerate until set, about 2 hours.
Garnish as desired.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger in frying pan. Add onion. Cook 1/2 bag noodles. Drain. Set aside. Add soup, garlic salt, tomato sauce and Ragu to hamburger.
Layer noodles and hamburger mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corn lite bread
directions: Sift meal, flour, sugar and salt together. Mix buttermilk and soda together; combine with dry ingredients and add shortening. Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except bacon bits.
Chill several hours.
Shape into ball and roll in bacon bits.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and vanilla. Continue beating until mix is thick. With spoon, stir in zucchini and pineapple. Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, chopped nuts and raisins. Stir gently until zucchini mixture is blended. Divide dough equally between 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil, buttermilk and soda, sifted with flour.
Mix well. Roll out and place in a 450° oven. It is not necessary to let rise.
Place remainder of dough in refrigerator in a covered bowl.

title: cake filling for banana cake
directions: Mix sugar,
milk,
butter
and
egg,
cook over low heat until it
thickens
and begins to bubble, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add pecans and coconut.

title: banana-chocolate chip muffins
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
In small bowl, combine egg, butter and milk.
Pour into flour mixture and stir just until moistened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Fill well-greased muffin tins almost full.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until done.
These muffins freeze well and can be microwaved after frozen.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Spread carrots in shallow baking dish.
Mix water or carrot liquid, onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; pour over carrots.
Top with mixture of bread crumbs or cracker crumbs, butter and paprika.
Bake in 375° oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add soups, rice and water.
Spread in baking dish.
Top with chicken breasts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dog cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add the rest and mix well.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn oven off and put all cookies back into oven to get hard (leave until oven is cooled).
Your dog will love them.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter with fork.
Add 1/2 cup pecans.
Pat into 9 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: oatmeal applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves; set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits and bread
in a
bowl.
Put enough hot water over bread to dissolve bread.
Stir in 1 cup sugar, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and a pinch of salt.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish sprayed with Pam and bake at 425° until done.
Remove from oven; let cool and slice.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hamburg vegetable casserole
directions: Fry hamburg with butter and diced onion until brown.
Add hot water to cover meat and add carrots and potatoes (both cubed) and boil slowly.
Salt and pepper to taste and cook until tender.
Add soy sauce.
Mix 2 to 3 tablespoons of flour in cold water and add to hamburg mixture.
Stir until thick.
Pour into casserole dish; cover with pie dough and bake until brown.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Make into balls.
Place in pan.
Mix brown sugar, dry mustard, vinegar and water thoroughly.
Pour over ham balls, basting often.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ole-time tea cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix sugar, butter and egg.
Add milk and soda mixture, flavoring, nutmeg and flour.
Roll out dough and cut into desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla, beat well.
Add flour with soda and cream of tartar.
Put into a cookie press using the cheese straw disk or refrigerate overnight and roll out.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs.
Heat oil in electric skillet at 360°.
Brown chicken on both sides, then remove to casserole.
Stir tomato sauce and herbs in pan.
Heat to boiling and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in butter and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Add Mozzarella cheese to top and bake 10 minutes uncovered.

title: frozen banana fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: pineapple casserole #1
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add pineapple, slightly beaten eggs and bread.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish sprayed with Pam. Do not cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook wild rice in broth or water until liquid is absorbed, about 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cool; add pecans, raisins, mint, onions and orange sections.
Set aside.
Combine orange rind, orange juice, oil, salt and pepper and mix well.
Pour over rice mix and toss. Let stand at room temperature 2 hours.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Drain the pineapple and reserve the juice.
Make cake per directions except substitute the pineapple juice for water.
If not enough juice, add water.
Bake in a 9 x 13 greased pan at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together with electric mixer and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Heat soup, cheese, gelatin and water until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased jello mold.
Chill in refrigerator several hours and remove from mold.
Place on platter with crackers to serve.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in salted water until tender; drain and slice. Saute onion, garlic, green pepper and parsley in bacon drippings. Remove from heat; add eggplant.
Soak bread in water; squeeze out excess liquid.
Add to eggplant mixture.
Add seafood; season to taste.
Place in well-greased casserole or baking shells.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: american chop suey
directions: Saute burger, onion and peppers until cooked.
Add soup, tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to directions.
Mix together and serve hot.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into 2 balls; roll into 1/2 cup nuts.
Can freeze and serve later.
Serve with crackers.

title: rhubarb cocktail
directions: Bring the rhubarb, sugar and water to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, or until thickness as desired.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer chicken and vegetables. Cover with gravy.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Take out and cover with crescent rolls, keeping dough in one piece.
Cook for additional 11 to 13 minutes at 375° or until crust is golden.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Roll out like biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. (Dough can be refrigerated.)

title: pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Fry bacon; drain and chop finely.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on party rye bread.
Broil for 10 minutes or until cheese melts and serve.
Half recipe 65 pieces.
Whole recipe 140 pieces.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef in butter; stir in tomato sauce, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Mix sour cream, green onions and noodles.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers and onions in jars. Let cool.
Put in refrigerator.

title: * chocolate cherry bars *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
By hand, stir until well mixed, the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Takes about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients, except for the Monterey Jack cheese. Serve in soup bowls topped with the cheese.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot patties
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the flour, parsley, onion, salt, pepper, Tabasco and lemon peel.
Stir in the eggs and carrots and mix well.
Drop the mixture by heaping tablespoonful into a lightly greased griddle or skillet.
Cook the patties over medium heat for about 5 minutes on each side or until brown.

title: fruit salad with pudding
directions: Mix with mixer.
Select any fruit desired for fruit salad. Chill, then serve.
Pudding sauce becomes thick.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cake will crack slightly on top.
Cool in pan for 1 hour before removing.
For the icing, use a cream cheese type topping, or none at all.

title: cabbage and pineapple slaw(low-fat)
directions: Mix cabbage, pineapple, raisins and apple in dish.
Mix mayonnaise with pineapple juice.
Pour this mixture over cabbage mixture.
Mix together and serve.
Keeps several days in the refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Save pineapple juice and add enough water to make 4 cups.
Cook pudding in this liquid instead of milk.
Cook until thick.
Let chill and stir in fruit.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mixed chocolate fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off foil.
Cut into squares.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Makes about 4 dozen pieces or 2 pounds.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Partially set Jell-O.
Add whipping cream, then pineapple and apples.
Refrigerate.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: Mix together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Add the carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple.
Beat in the eggs, oil and vanilla.
Fill paper lined muffin cups and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 20 muffins.

title: nanny's cheddar cheese ball
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients. Save 1/2 cup pecans and 1/4 cup parsley to garnish. Add the rest of the pecans and parsley to cheese mixture. Shape into a ball. Wrap in Saran Wrap. Refrigerate overnight. Garnish about 1 hour before serving.

title: apple-pineapple slaw
directions: Combine and toss until mayonnaise coats all ingredients. Serve in lettuce-lined bowl. Trim with lemon juice sprinkled unpared apple wedges. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blonde mini-kiss squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
In bowl, beat butter and brown sugar; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients and gradually add to butter mixture. Beat until well blended.
Stir in chocolate mini-kisses.
Spread batter in pan; sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: crazy cake(no eggs)
directions: Sift dry ingredients into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Makes 3 holes.
In one hole, put 1 tablespoon vinegar and in one hole put 1/2 cup vegetable oil and in one hole, put 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Over all of this, pour 1 cup cold water.
Mix well.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange prunes
directions: Prepare jello according to directions on box; put in 9 inch glass pan.
Stuff prunes with cottage cheese.
Let jello set up a bit then insert prunes into jello.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter or margarine, milk and marshmallows in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved and marshmallows are melted.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring all the time.
Add chocolate and stir until entirely melted.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: magic butter rolls
directions: Sift flour and measure.
To 1 1/2 cups flour, add salt and shortening.
Combine as for pie crust.
Combine milk and hot water.
When lukewarm, add yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar; blend well, then stir into flour, salt and shortening, beating until very smooth.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes, then add beaten eggs and beat vigorously.
Beat in vanilla (1 teaspoon) and flour (remaining 1 1/2 cups).
Stir until smooth.
Tie dough loosely in a square of cheesecloth and drop into a pail of cool water (70° to 80°).
In about an hour or less, the dough will rise to top of pail.
Remove and turn onto a platter.
Cut pieces the size of an egg using a tablespoon.
Roll each one in cup of sugar and chopped nuts (some cinnamon if desired).
Twist into figure eight and place on greased baking sheet.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake in hot oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not put too close together.

title: goo goo bars
directions: Mix together.
Make a patty and freeze.
Makes 1 serving.

title: easy baked potato soup
directions: Peel (or you can leave peels on) and dice the baked potatoes. Set aside. In Dutch oven or soup kettle, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Using slotted spoon, remove bacon to paper towel. Drain, reserving 1-1/2 teaspoon drippings. Add soups, milk, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce, onion powder, pepper and potatoes to the drippings. Cook uncovered for 10 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally. Stir in sour cream and cook for 1-2 minutes or until heated through - do not boil. Garnish with cheddar cheese and bacon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Beat egg, add soup (no water) only and 1 cup mayonnaise.
Mix all together.
Then add to drained broccoli.
Mix in the cheese.
Add onion (optional).

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan combine butter, sugar and water; bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup chocolate morsels and vanilla extract.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chocolate morsels and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
While hot, spread top with 1 jar Marshmallow Creme; while warm, frost with chocolate icing.
Cool completely. Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares.
Makes 16.

title: bridie's really great chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a single layer in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, leek or onion, wine and lemon juice in a medium-sized bowl.
Spoon sauce over the chicken pieces.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour, or until chicken is tender and richly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mound cake(top money maker at auction)
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups of sugar, adding eggs one at a time. Beat after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put in 8 1/2 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted oleo.
Cover the top of the casserole with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ansley's microwave fudge
directions: Sift sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add milk; mix until partially blended.
Cut up margarine or butter over top. Microwave on High 2 minutes until bottom of dish feels warm to touch.
Remove from microwave.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth. Add nuts.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Beat egg, water and vinegar together and add to flour mixture.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Saute 1 tablespoon onion or more in butter.
Add all ingredients to cooked rice.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Melt margarine and cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over water and stir until dissolved.
Add butter, eggs and sugar to yeast mixture.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Dough will be the consistency of waffle batter.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins and bake at 375°
for 10 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese, pudding, milk and Cool Whip in mixer. Layer cookies and pudding mix in a new 6-inch or 7-inch flowerpot or plastic container.
Keep enough crumbs to sprinkle on the top. For added decoration arrange artificial flower stems in the middle of the "Dirt Dessert."

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make the night before.
Stir occasionally.
Great colors for Christmastime.

title: grandma ferry's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into flour and then on sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: make-ahead potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Drain and mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion and salt.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan or several smaller ones.
Drizzle with melted butter. Sprinkle with paprika (optional).
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; no need to defrost.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix pineapple and pie filling in the cake pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the fruit.
Cover entire cake with thin slivers of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
Shape into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.

title: cinnamon crisps or elephant ears
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir until shortening melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
Add milk mixture and egg to dry ingredients, mixing at low mixer speed.
Beat 30 seconds on low speed.
Scrape bowl and beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough (1 to 1 1/2 cups).
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Combine 1/4 cup butter, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon.
Divide in half.
Set aside.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs. Beat well! Mix dry ingredients together (not oatmeal) and stir in. Add the vanilla and oatmeal; mix well. Shape into long roll or two and chill for several hours or overnight. Cut into slices. Bake 15 minutes in 325° to 350° oven. Makes 5 dozen.

title: milwaukee pork chops
directions: Sear chops on both sides until brown.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and let simmer until chops are tender, at least one hour.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix egg, sugar and oil; add to yeast mixture.
Make a hole in flour.
Pour in wet ingredients.
Knead.
Form into rolls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Brush tops lightly with oil. May sprinkle with sesame seed, if desired.
Let rolls rise.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned.
Easy and delicious!

title: leola's shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: Put fresh shrimp in 1 pint of water with 1 teaspoon salt. Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Turn off heat and leave covered 3 minutes.
Drain and reserve liquid for gumbo.
In a large pot with heavy bottom, add flour to heated oil.
Cook and stir constantly, until deep golden brown. Take pot away from heat and quickly add onions and garlic; cook 4 minutes on low heat.
Add bell peppers and bay leaf.
Combine broth with remaining water.

title: cranberry glazed rolls
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Grease muffin pans or custard cups. Sprinkle a few chopped nuts into each.
Combine cranberry sauce that has been crushed with a fork and brown sugar.
Place a tablespoon of the mixture in each muffin cup.
Then turn Brown 'N Serve rolls upside-down and press into each muffin cup.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool for 4 to 5 minutes.
Invert pans and gently remove rolls.

title: stove top sweet potatoes
directions: Combine into frying pan the butter, brown sugar, orange juice, syrup, vanilla and apple rings.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
While this is cooking, boil sweet potatoes, then peel them and put into syrup mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: confetti squares
directions: Pinch the crescent rolls together to make a crust. Bake them and set them aside to cool. Mix together mayonnaise, Ranch dressing mix and cream cheese. Spread over cooled crust. Chop the carrots, celery, broccoli, red bell pepper, yellow bell pepper and onions (chop these by hand). Pat the vegetables dry with paper towel. Mix them in bowl, then sprinkle over the crust. Lightly pat vegetables into the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Sprinkle a little Parmesan cheese on top. Cut into small squares and refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Cut up eggs and onion.
Add pimentos and salad cublets.
Mix this up real good.

title: cocoa-cola cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine sugar and flour.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine oil, butter, cocoa and cola.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add chocolate mixture to sugar mixture and beat until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well; bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Nut Frosting.

title: meatballs with potatoes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and make into small meatballs; brown and drain.
Place in bottom of large Dutch oven and top with onions and potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour tomato soup and water over this and cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: snicker bar cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on box. Pour 1/2 the batter in a well-greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. In microwave, melt caramels, milk and butter; stir until smooth. Pour over first 1/2 of cake. Layer on nuts and coconut. Pour remaining 1/2 of batter over the top and bake for another 20 minutes. Let cool before cutting.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare rice as directed on box.

title: finger jello(another version!)
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1 cup cold water.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add remaining ingredients, including dissolved Knox gelatine.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Heat all ingredients together.
Put chicken in baking dish. Pour enough sauce over chicken to marinate it.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Grill and baste with sauce until done. The sauce you don't use can be kept in refrigerator.

title: apple delight cake
directions: Place apple filling in large pan (9 x 13-inches). Sprinkle cake mix over filling, then layer of pecans and almonds. Melt butter and pour over top evenly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together all the ingredients, except the onion rings, and put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Cover the pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add one egg yolk at a time.
Beat; dissolve chocolate in boiling water, then add to mixture flour and milk alternately.
Add soda to last 1/3 cup milk, then add to mixture.
Add vanilla and salt, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: the golden egg
directions: Hard-cook the eggs and peel.
Heat on stove the rest of the ingredients. Add eggs and liquid. Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: First mix shortening, sugar and eggs, then add remaining ingredients (flour should be added a little at a time to prevent clumps and to make even).
Make dough into small balls.
Place a few at a time in a bowl with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar.
Place lid on bowl and shake until dough is covered.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Great around Christmastime.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, butter, eggs and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth. Add rhubarb.
Let stand while you prepare pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° and 30 minutes at 350°.
This is good with a crumb topping instead of top crust.

title: baked pepper chicken with hot sauce
directions: Wash chicken well.
Remove and save neck and giblets.
Mix the following ingredients to make the marinade:
vinegar, lemon concentrate, salt, cumin, black pepper and garlic.

title: fire storm bar-b-que sauce
directions: Heat the pot with oil and saute the onions until they are translucent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly on medium to medium low heat for 1 to 2 hours.
Keep to a boil, being careful not to scorch.
Sauce will thicken as it cooks down.
Pour into container and seal.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps for several weeks.
Sauce is hearty and very spicy.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Melt Crisco; cool.
Mix water, sugar and yeast; dissolve thoroughly. Stir together dry ingredients in a large bowl.
To the flour mixture, add shortening and water/yeast mixture all at once.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread with softened butter, fold and re-roll. Cut into squares or rounds and place close together on baking pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Add 1 tablespoonful (heaping) to 1 cup boiling water.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts. Top each with cheese and ham.
Roll and secure with toothpick.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef, loosening to fine particles.
Add onion, green pepper and spices.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add tomato sauce and simmer slowly 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the chili beans and cook until bubbly.
Place on center of tortilla and roll up.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies until they look like dirt.
Cream oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding with milk, add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer mixture in flower pot, first cookies, then cream mixture, etc., ending with cookies on top.
Cool 3 to 4 hours.
Use plastic pot that has a dish under. Cover hole in bottom with foil.
Put artificial flower on top and serve with small garden shovel.

title: cheesy bread bites
directions: Cut biscuits into small pieces and place in 9 x 13 pan. Melt 1 stick of butter and Blue cheese. Pour over biscuit bites and cook at 375° until biscuits are done, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk, pancake mix, sugar and vanilla in a medium sized bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Heat oil to 375° in heavy skillet or deep fryer.
Spoon 1/4 cup batter into a funnel.
Hold finger over funnel hole.
Release into a pan, but have anything round (not plastic) to keep the mixture in a round shape; fry until a golden brown on both sides.
Put topping on it.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice over bottom of baking pan.
Pour onion soup over rice.
Add water.
Wash and dry chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place over rice.
Spread cream of celery soup over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add water as necessary to keep moist.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Preheat gas oven to 350°.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Beat well and bake in a well-greased rectangular pan, lightly floured, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cornflakes candy
directions: Put syrup and sugar in pan.
Bring to good boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Blend well.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool slightly, then cut into squares.
Makes 15 squares.

title: raw veggie salad
directions: Mix ingredients day before.

title: raisin oatmeal mini scones
directions: In a large bowl, combine margarine and oats.
Stir in egg substitute, vanilla, and sweetener.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Add to oat mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheets coated with non stick cooking spray.
Bake at 400 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until browned.

title: date bar
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ham and cooked potatoes together. Pour soup over mixture; add milk.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: braised honey chicken wings
directions: Cut each wing at joints, in 3 sections.
Save tips for broth or other use.
In hot oil, in heavy skillet, stir-fry onions and ginger 3 minutes to flavor oil.
Remove with slotted spoon; discard.
Brown chicken; set aside.
Drain skillet.
Add sherry, honey and soy sauce; bring to a boil.
Stir in chicken; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Uncover and simmer 5 minutes, turning chicken frequently as sauce thickens.
Serve immediately with any remaining sauce or arrange on platter; cover.
Chill.
Serve cold.
Makes 6 appetizer servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and almond extract.
Beat in the egg yolks one at a time.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Add alternately with crushed berries.
Beat egg whites stiff. Fold in.
Line a loaf pan with greased wax paper.
Pour in the batter.
