Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness with cake tester.
This bread is very good toasted, too.

title: applecrunch
directions: Sprinkle cinnamon over apples and pour butter over crunch mixture.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and 2/3 cup of milk.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add remaining milk, vanilla and whole eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown hamburger.
Add noodles, mixed vegetables and tomato soup.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour. Can also be mixed in a frypan and heated on the stove.

title: luncheon cocktail
directions: Mix rum and cranberry juice.
Pour into punch bowl and add sherbet; mix.
Makes 10 cups.

title: spicy almond chicken
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook about 10 minutes, or until lightly browned on all sides. Place chicken in a lightly greased (I use cooking spray) 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add the remaining ingredients to the skillet; cook over medium heat until currant jelly dissolves, stirring occasionally.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake an additional 10 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: almond-orange biscotti
directions: Spray baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder in large bowl.
Make well in center.
To the well add remaining ingredients; with hands work until dough is formed.
Divide in half.
Shape into 2 flat-bottomed cylinders, 1-inch high x 2 1/2-inches wide x 8-inches long.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium for 3 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Fry onion in bacon grease.
Add flour and sugar, mix well.
Then add water and vinegar.
Mix in with potatoes.
Put in 350° oven to heat through.
Multiply recipe by 6 to fill a crock using 1 pound of bacon.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake sugar (1 cup) and cinnamon together in Baggie. Cut biscuits into quarters with scissors. Shake a few at a time in cinnamon sugar.
Layer biscuit quarters and nuts in a large Bundt pan.
Melt margarine. Stir in sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits and nuts in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool a few minutes.
Invert on serving plate. Serve hot.
May halve recipe for small Bundt pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil in blender.
Blend constantly, while slowly adding oil.
Refrigerate.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and layer pecans and coconut in pan.
Pour batter over pecans and coconut.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar and pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Add milk; cook slowly until it begins to thicken.
Add beaten egg yolks and stir.
When fully boiled it is done.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown lightly in 375° oven.

title: cocoa meringue pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together dry.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of water.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Heat milk and water; pour over the egg mixture. Return to double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: crepes
directions: Combine first five ingredients in container of electric blender; process 30 seconds.
Scrape down sides of blender container and process a second time.
Refrigerate batter for 1 hour.

title: apricot spice bars
directions: Mix
butter
and
brown sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add egg, milk,
lemon juice and vanilla; mix until blended.
Sift flour, soda
and
cinnamon together.
Add to creamed mixture. Beat
until blended.
Stir
in
apricots,
nuts
and coconut. Spread
in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost.

title: pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and beat until thick.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: david's favorite
directions: Boil first five ingredients together.
When cooked, drain and set aside.
Brown sausage, salt and pepper in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, water, brown sugar and mustard.
Add 2 mixtures together and simmer 15 minutes.
Add rice.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil chicken with celery, onion and parsley. Cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook either a full head of fresh broccoli, cut up into flowerets, or the frozen.
Place broccoli into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place chicken pieces on top.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over the top.
You may want to sprinkle crushed croutons on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Even the kids that hate broccoli love this one!

title: seafood fantasy
directions: Layer seafood in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt cheeses, mix with Ro-Tel, then pour over seafood.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve over pasta or rice.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix and next 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer 1 or 2 minutes. Press 1/2 of cake mix mixture into bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels and drizzle with condensed milk.
Sprinkle with remaining cake mix mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: shepard's pie
directions: Brown beef in hot fat.
Add onions and green pepper, cook until tender, but not brown.
Stir in soup and place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle peas and carrots over.
Arrange mashed potatoes in a ring on top, allowing filling to show through and drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven (350°) until heated through, about 25 minutes.

title: aunt ruth's torte
directions: Beat eggs together.
Mix with other ingredients in the order listed.
Bake in greased loaf pan 2 1/2 hours in a 250° oven. Slice very thinly after loaf has cooled.
Makes one 9 x 5-inch loaf or 2 small size foil pans.

title: seafoam jello salad
directions: Save juice from both fruits.
Bring 1 cup mandarin orange juice to boil.
Pour over jello and stir until dissolved.
Let set until jelly stage.
Add oranges and crushed pineapple; add some of pineapple juice to cream cheese.
Add to jello and fold in Cool Whip.

title: butterscotch yum yum
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1/2 cup of nuts; pat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate delight
directions: To make crust, melt oleo and mix in flour and chopped pecans. Press into a long baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
With an electric mixer, mix chocolate and vanilla puddings with milk.
Spread on other layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Grate chocolate chips and spread on top.

title: birmingham slaw dressing
directions: Mix well and serve over finely shredded coleslaw mixture.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
(Optional:
Cut along back of shrimp to butterfly for larger appearance and fancier looking shrimp.)

title: hawaiian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, mixed with baking powder, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: plum pudding sauce
directions: Cream butter, egg and sugar.
Add wine and cook in double boiler until thick.
Store in jar and can be reheated, if you like the sauce warm. Can be served with fruitcake, applesauce cake or whatever you prefer to serve on.

title: corn mazatlan
directions: Drain corn, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid.
Combine liquid and cream cheese in saucepan.
Heat and blend until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans and place in a large bowl.
Add all the other ingredients and stir well.
Chill for 2 hrs. or longer.

title: spiritual awareness
directions: My recipe for spiritual awareness calls for several key ingredients as listed.
I begin by mixing ample portions of faith and strength.
Next, add a dash of love and a smidgen of peace. This is closely followed by a heaping cup of conviction and a healthy measure of understanding.
After stirring these together, I then add generous scoops of receptivity and joy.
The recipe continues with confidence, generosity, acceptance and last, but certainly not least, a helping of contentment.
The ingredients are then thoroughly mixed, and my spiritual awareness begins to rise.
I am filled with a sense of peace, for I am one with God. I enjoy an expanded spiritual awareness that satisfies every longing of my soul.
Thank you, God!

title: scampi primavera
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Heat oil in large skillet; cook and stir garlic and lemon peel about 30 seconds.
Add vegetables and shrimp and cook and stir over medium heat until shrimp turn pink, about 4 or 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir in basil and parsley.
Drain pasta.
Spoon mixture over pasta and toss well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy beef roll-ups
directions: *Round steak should be cut 1/2 inch thick.

title: chocolate coconut candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, oleo, coconut and pecans. This makes a very thick mixture.
Shape into small balls and place a toothpick in each one.
Put on wax paper.
Chill.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax together.
Dip candy in mixture.

title: island potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly, press into bowl and chill.
Unmold on serving platter.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in deep pie crust.
Cook 15 minutes in 425° oven; then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to package and drain.
Mix soup and sour cream together. Add vegetables.
In a separate bowl, mix dry stuffing with melted butter.
Put half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then spread vegetable mixture on top.
Then add remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chimichangas
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients, except tortillas. Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer about 2 to 3 hours or until meat is very tender.
Uncover and boil rapidly about 15 minutes or until water has almost evaporated.
Remove from heat.
Using two forks, shred meat very fine.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1/2 package of beef.
Form into ball. Roll in remaining chopped beef.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Start in cold oven.

title: hamburg and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburg, celery and onion.
Add soups, soy sauce, rice and 2 cups water.
Bake in 2-quart casserole dish, sprayed with Pam, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add cocoa.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Add sugar alternately with milk.
Blend in vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Makes 2 cups of frosting.

title: caramel chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water, brown sugar and butter in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Mixture will be thick.
Stir in chocolate chips (and nuts).
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 24 to 27 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely in pan.
Cut into bars.
Brickle chips or caramel toppings may be used if desired.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy with mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour; stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° or lower for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix ingredients in medium size saucepan.
Cook at hard boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add 1/2 cup peanut butter (chunky or smooth); beat hard.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 cups oatmeal (uncooked).
Mix well.
Drop spoonful onto wax paper to cool and harden.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix and let rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll 1/2 inch thick or more and cut with a pizza cutter.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Dip bread stick on both sides and lay on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, sesame seeds, poppy seeds, parsley, red pepper, minced onion, or a combination of your favorites. Raise 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter bark candy
directions: Melt white chocolate, peanut chips and peanut butter until smooth.
Add nuts and pretzels and stir.
Pour onto cookie sheet covered with foil.
Put in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Take out and check to see if it's firm.
If so, break and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped potatoes and cheese sauce
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in salted water for 5 minutes and then drain.
Stir soup with milk until smooth.
Put one-half of potatoes in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half of soup. Add remaining potatoes and cover with remaining soup.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and then uncover.
Bake for 15 more minutes.
Baking temperature should be 350°.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix ingredients together. Roll out on flat surface. Make sure to flour underneath and on top.
Let dry 5 to 6 hours.
Cut out on surface and let dry 1 hour more.
Add to boiling soup or water.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Beat the chili seasoning, cream cheese and salsa.
Shape.
Top with chopped nuts and Monterey Jack cheese.
Chill until firm. Serve with assorted crackers and vegetables.

title: almond crescent cookies
directions: Whirl almonds in blender.
Mix flour, sugar and ground almonds.
With fingers, work in butter and vanilla until mixture cleans bowl.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Roll dough into balls (approximately 1 1/4-inch), then into rolls (3 1/2-inch).
Form into crescent shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool on pan about 10 minutes.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 25 to 30.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, onion, pepper, celery and garlic.
Add beans with liquid, tomatoes and paste, chili powder and salt.
Stir.
Cook 1 hour on medium to low heat.

title: cereal coconut crisps
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Pour onto waxed paper.
Add baking powder, soda and salt to flour.
Stir well to blend.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together butter, eggs and cake mix.
Put in cake pan, 13 x 9-inch Pyrex, and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't open stove door while baking until time is up.

title: philadelphia cream cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover; put in refrigerator and let stand 48 hours.
Serve on crackers.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add 1 can each of cream of chicken and mushroom soup, chicken broth, green chilies and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bone and chop boiled chicken and add to this mixture. Line a large baking dish with flour tortillas.
Add a layer of chicken mixture, then cheese.
Repeat layering with tortillas and mixture; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Coat potato strips with mixture.
Melt one	stick
margarine in large baking dish or pan. Arrange potatoes
in
melted margarine.
Bake in 400° oven	for 30 minutes.
Turn
potatoes
and
bake
30	minutes longer.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook noodles separately. Mix other ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste. Mix noodles with soup and simmer.

title: fruit crisp
directions: *Rhubarb, apples, plums or peaches (your choice).

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients thoroughly and let stand 2 hours. Drain.
Do not rinse!
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and put in freezer containers; freeze. When ready to use, just thaw and serve.

title: strawberry snowdrift
directions: Combine milk, strawberries, sugar, lime juice and ice in an electric blender.
Whirl until thick and frothy.
If desired wet rim of glasses with lemon wedge and dip in sugar.
Pour drink into glasses.
Makes about 3 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Chop lettuce.
Add chopped tomato. Add hamburger and onion.
Crumble taco chips; add to mixture. Cube cheese and add.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: pecan pie bar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Press mixture firmly into bottom and 1/4-inch up sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: monkey pod bread
directions: Roll cut biscuits in cinnamon and 1 1/2 cups sugar mixture. Place in Bundt pan.
Heat butter, 3/4 cup sugar plus any leftover sugar mixture until dissolved.
Drizzle over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: white grape juice tea
directions: Dissolve sugar in lemon juice and white grape juice.
Pour mixture in a gallon container.
Finish gallon with unsweetened tea.
Serve cold.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in bananas.
Add flours and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: corn bake
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Beat eggs lightly with a fork.
Add sugar, flour and milk; mix.
Add corn; pour into dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles with butter in broth.
When done, add chicken, soup, onion and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish. Top with frozen loaf bread dipped in butter.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well together the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together and mix in.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, checking for doneness with a toothpick.
Do not overbake.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: herb and garlic butter
directions: In small bowl, combine butter, Italian seasoning, ground red pepper and garlic.
Can be used on sliced French bread and toasted in oven at 350° until toasted.
Goes great with spaghetti type dinner.

title: russian dressing
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Place in a long 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish (glass).
Sprinkle Velveeta cheese on top. Place in oven at 350° and bake until soups bubble.
Place aluminum foil on top loosely to prevent cheese from burning. Serves 6.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Heat oven at 375°.
Grease pans.
Beat eggs and sugar in bowl. Beat in bananas, raisins, oil and vanilla.
Let stand a minute or two.
Thoroughly mix flour and bran, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Add banana mixture.
Fold into dry ingredients.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 regular or 48 miniature.

title: butterscotch chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl. Stir in chips and pecans. Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8-10 min. or until centers are just set. Let stand for 2 min. Cool completely.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: If double mixture, use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Mix
the
first
ingredients.
Add
egg and vanilla. Beat the
next 3 ingredients and add to mixture.
Take pieces of
dough and
roll	into
balls
larger
than a nickel.
Use miniature muffin tins.
Place a ball in each cup.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes. Remove
from
oven	and immediately push a miniature peanut butter cup into each ball.
Replace in oven for approximately 5 minutes. Let
cool before removing from pan.
Makes 36 to 40.

title: overnight potato bake
directions: Boil potatoes and mash with butter and cream cheese. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate mixture overnight in a buttered casserole dish. Bake next day in 350 degree oven for 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: "hot onion dip"
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease a medium baking dish. Mix together all ingredients. Pour into baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned. Makes 6 cups (48 servings).

title: mexican crinkle cookies
directions: Cream together
the shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in syrup and chocolate.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon into cream mixture;
stir
to
make
stiff
dough.
Shape in 1-inch balls and roll
in
sugar.
Place
balls on ungreased sheet, 3 inches apart. Bake
in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar slowly.
Continue beating until very light.
Fold in the dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add melted butter and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 5 tablespoons of melted butter over top of cake batter.
Blend 1/2 cup sugar with 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. (I bake at 375°.)

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
In a 4-quart kettle, heat margarine, flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk. Add vegetables.

title: mock pigs-in-the-blanket
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Arrange half the cabbage in casserole.
Top with beef and onion.
Layer rest of cabbage.
Pour soup over top.
Cover casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: rice cooker jambalaya
directions: Put all ingredients in rice cooker.
When the bell rings, wait 1/2 hour, then it's ready to eat.
Very good.

title: homemade butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and salt.
Put this in saucepan or double boiler.
Add 2 cups milk and mix.
Beat 2 egg yolks.
Add to saucepan, stirring until thick.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes. Add 2 tablespoons butter or margarine, vanilla extract and maple flavoring.
Cool and pour in ready baked pie crust.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Wash pork and drain.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and Mrs.
Dash and Accent in a bowl.
Roll the meat in flour mixture.
Brown on all sides in hot oil.
After browning, place in glass baking dish and pour sweet and sour sauce over meat.
Cook at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together;
pour
in
greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 1
hour
or until toothpick comes out clean when you stick it in cake.

title: ba-yama
directions: Alternate layers of yams and bananas in a 1-quart casserole, ending with a layer of yams.
Stir together salt, corn syrup and orange juice.
Pour over yams and bananas.
Cover and bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, pour off oil and sprinkle casserole with coconut.
Return to oven for 10 minutes to brown coconut.
Serves 6.

title: treatwiches
directions: *Sprinkles,
cookie
crumbs,
chocolate
chips, chopped nuts, diced fruit, toasted coconut, miniature marshmallows and assorted candies.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Combine ingredients and serve with carrots, celery, cucumbers, etc.

title: spanakopita (spinach pie)(greek)
directions: Wash thoroughly and drain the spinach well.
(May use food processor.)
Sprinkle with salt.
Squeeze spinach to drain all water.
Saute onions, parsley, dill and fennel in a frying pan. Let cool.
Beat the eggs.
Cut the cheese, then mix all together with spinach.
Brush each sheet of fillo with butter and place in pan 8 to 10 layers.
Put your mixture in pan and add remaining 8 to 10 sheets of fillo on top.
Brush each with butter as you go along. Fold edges under and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Preparation time: 30 minutes.

title: holiday delight
directions: Mix all in punch bowl, adding ginger ale last.
Garnish as desired.

title: canadian chicken
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Roll corned
beef with chicken on outside.
Cover each with a slice of
bacon.
Bake,
uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.
Pour on gravy and bake, covered, for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Beat together egg, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt until well blended.
Stir in apple and nuts.
Turn into 8-inch greased pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: dieter vegetable soup
directions: Chop all vegetables coarsely.
Add water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: cheesy broccoli(microwave)
directions: On microwave-safe serving platter, place unwrapped frozen broccoli, icy side up.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Rearrange so that broccoli stalks are to the outside of platter.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Let stand, covered, while making cheese sauce.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients into it and knead. Give each child a ball of dough to roll and twist into any shape. Lay on greased cookie sheets.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf with vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Dust with flour and a dash of pepper.
Brown meat in butter in a large skillet.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Brown all lightly.
Stir in beef consomme. Cover and cook for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Gradually stir in sour cream; cook 5 minutes.
Serve over 3 cups of cooked noodles.
(Can be served individually.)

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, parsley and seasonings.
Dip chicken in butter and then crumb mixture.
Arrange in a single layer in a shallow pan.
Pour any remaining butter over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: banana brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine cake mix and butter; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
Press remaining cake mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices over mixture.
Blend sour cream and egg together; spread over apples.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a rapid boil; remove from heat.
Add butterscotch instant pudding and quick cooking oatmeal. Mix thoroughly.
Cool 15 minutes and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll out dough and cut cookies.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours; stir several times.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to the directions on the box.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Meanwhile, melt caramels with 1 cup milk.
After 10 minutes, pour caramel mix, chocolate chips and nuts over cake.
Add remaining batter.
Bake another 17 to 20 minutes. No icing is necessary.

title: orange sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Simmer and stir until slightly thick and transparent (about 5 minutes).

title: baked shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine first 9 ingredients in shallow 2 quart baking dish and mix well.
Remove 1/4 cup of this mixture and set aside.
Add shrimp to baking dish and mix thoroughly. Combine breadcrumbs with reserved butter sauce and sprinkle over shrimp.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix Philadelphia cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Add shrimp and other ingredients.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Let cool.
Mix Crisco, sugar, milk, salt and vanilla.
Beat at low speed 5 minutes.
Add powdered sugar and beat 2 to 3 minutes more.
Split cake using a thread.
Spread mixture between layers.
Ice cake with chocolate icing.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients, and stir just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pans two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 1 dozen.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon and rest of the ingredients together.
Fry in skillet until brown. Serve with sauce or mushroom soup.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Note:
Any fruit you like that's in season.

title: frosted apple squares
directions: Mix shortening, flour and salt as for pie crust.
Add enough milk to egg yolk to measure 2/3 cup liquid.
Add liquid to shortening mixture and stir quickly with fork.
Turn on floured board.
Knead 2 to 3 times.
Divide in half.
Roll to fit jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Spread apples along with sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter.
Roll out remaining crust and place on top, tucking in edges.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Prepare glaze.

title: broccoli-rice casserole(usa)
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix milk, soup, water and cheese together.
Stir in uncooked rice and the drained broccoli-onion mixture. Put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring once.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy chocolate chip dessert
directions: Pour milk in bowl.
Dip each chocolate chip cookie in milk. Layer cookies, after dipping one at a time.
Next, layer Cool Whip.
Add another layer of cookies, another layer of Cool Whip, etc. until bowl is filled, ending with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crush cookies and blend in butter.
Line a 9-inch pan with crumbs, reserving 2 tablespoons of crumbs for topping.
Chill.

title: french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Take butter and melt in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix in blender the eggs, milk, flour, salt and vanilla. Pour the mixture over the melted butter and cook until golden brown in oven, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corngroves, texas
directions: Mix corn, milk and seasonings.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Place in baking dish, layer crumbs on bottom and top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and soda.
Add the pineapple, eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan and cook 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven or test with a toothpick.
Let cool some, then cover with the icing.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake in long pan for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry pudding parfaits
directions: Prepare pudding by package directions.
Cool, then chill. Fold in the chilled rice, spices, whipped cream and orange rind. Spoon alternating layers of rice pudding and filling into parfait glasses.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Wash and core apples and pears, peeling if desired.
Cut into one inch chunks.
Slice bananas.
Wash grapes and cut in half. Combine fruits and almonds in salad bowl.
Mix yogurt with spices and cider.
Pour over fruit salad and stir to coat and chill. Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 21 g, protein 3 g, fat 6 g, calories 141.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Add marshmallows, Rice Krispies and M&M's.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until cool.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, flour, milk, eggs and salt. Cook over medium heat stirring constantly for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat in hot oil in large skillet.
Mix together flour, paprika, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir into meat mixture. Add onions, tomatoes and water.
Cover, simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir Pet milk into hot mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: coconut mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased or Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top with sesame seed and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Slice and enjoy.

title: apple potato pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Season pork chops with garlic salt and pepper.
Brown in hot skillet. Wash the potatoes and slice in rounds. Peel and slice apples in wedges.
Slice onion in rounds. Layer in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan in order: potatoes (salt and pepper), onion, chops, apples.
Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over the apples. Cover and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 325° and bake for another 45 minutes.
Uncover to baste and brown.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter/margarine.
Pat into bottom of 9x13 pan.
Freeze 20 minutes.

title: orange almond salad
directions: Brown almonds and sugar in a skillet; sugar will melt and coat almonds.
Tear lettuce.
Toss lettuce with celery and onions.

title: spinach mandarin salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients for dressing.
Place remaining items in a bowl. Pour dressing over salad just before serving.

title: country baked steaks
directions: Salt and pepper steaks, then dust with flour.
Brown quickly in a small amount of oil.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour soup and water over steaks.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Grind vegetables and add salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix with remaining and blend well.
Let stand 1 hour, then put in jars and seal.
Makes 9 pints.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour in a casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Place Ritz crackers on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° in oven for 45 minutes.

title: tara steak diane
directions: Coat one side of steak with mustard.
Sprinkle with pepper. Roll steak to coat both sides with mustard.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Cook shallots and garlic until soft.
Stir in mushrooms, steak sauce, 1 teaspoon mustard, capers and broth. Cook to reduce slightly.
Unroll steak.
Place in sauce and cook as desired, turning once.
Pour Irish Mist over all and ignite carefully.
When flame dies, serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat
soup and cream cheese together. Stir until smooth. Mix Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup water. Let set 5 minutes. Add mayonnaise to soup mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into lightly sprayed mold. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix soda in buttermilk.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add soda and buttermilk mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pie is firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir liquids together and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Baste occasionally.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in small bowl and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Mix until smooth.
Blend dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture. Roll mixture into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in sugar/cinnamon mixture until covered.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes (cookies will puff up at first, then flatten out).
Cool on cooling rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour and salt, then lemon juice and rind.
Stir in egg yolks and milk (beaten together).
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into a greased casserole; set casserole in pan of water and bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly onions
directions: Simmer onion rings in butter in a heavy pan over moderate heat until tender, stirring frequently.
Arrange onions in 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Top with cheese.
In a saucepan, heat soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper, stirring until well blended.
Pour over cheese and onions.
Stir lightly to allow sauce to mix thoroughly.
Top with buttered bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen and thawed at room temperature, then baked according to directions.

title: red onion salad
directions: Peel and slice onions.
Peel and section oranges.
Break romaine into serving pieces.
Arrange romaine in bowl.
Add orange sections and tiny beets.
Top with onion rings.
Combine oil, vinegar, orange juice, salt and seasonings; blend well.
Pour over salad; toss at moment of serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together eggs and cream cheese.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Stir in oats.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Stir in walnuts; set aside.
In small bowl, blend milk, vanilla and egg until well blended.
Stir in bananas until well mixed.
Add milk-banana mixture to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until loaf is golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Wrap in foil.
Let stand overnight in a cool, dry place before serving. Makes 1 loaf.

title: steak soup(from plaza iii in kansas city)
directions: Place butter in soup pot and melt without browning.
Add flour and stir constantly to form a smooth paste.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.

title: deep-dish apple danish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan or skillet. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.

Combine flour and 2 tablespoons sugar in a medium mixing bowl; cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine egg, vanilla and dissolved yeast; stir into flour mixture. Pat two-thirds of dough in bottom of a greased 9-inch square pan. Spread apple filling evenly over dough.
Roll remaining one-third of dough into a 9-inch square on a well floured surface; place over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake 25 minutes.
Drizzle with Sugar Glaze.

title: cottage ranch dip
directions: In blender, mix cottage cheese and Ranch powder dressing. Spoon into serving bowl and refrigerate until well chilled.
Place in center of serving platter surrounded by veggies.
Delicious. You don't have to tell them what it's made from.
Jerry hates cottage cheese, but he loves this dip.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Save 1/2 of margarine.
Mix with corn flakes. Mix all remaining ingredients in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Top with flakes and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all together.
Put in rice cooker.
After the bell rings, let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir and let stand until time to eat.

title: simple pie crust
directions: Cut oleo into flour.
Add milk; knead lightly.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes a 2-crust 9-inch pie.

title: red cake(this is a must for christmas.)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add salt, buttermilk, flour, and vanilla.
Remove from mixer and mix in but don't beat--the vinegar and soda.
Pour into two 8 inch round cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Split layers in half.
Frost with icing.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt. Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out all liquid.
Add carrot and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over slaw mixture and put in freezer.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Melt butter; allow to cool.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add potatoes, butter and eggs and finally milk last.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) deep dish shells.
Bake at 300° (at least) for 1 hour.

title: luncheon shrimp curry
directions: Halve the shrimp lengthwise.
Cook onion and celery in butter until almost tender.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Add shrimp. Simmer uncovered, stirring frequently, about 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: elizabeth salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 Cup hot water and cool.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased mold and chill. (Large bowl may be used)
Serve topped with sour cream, if desired.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread into a lightly greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
May frost with a lemon glaze.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add the tea bags and steep.
Take out tea bags and add the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.

title: mccoskey's potato soup
directions: Peel and slice thin 8 medium potatoes.
Add onion, margarine and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with water and boil until tender.
Pour milk over potatoes and bring to boil.
Stir and set off burner.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook a whole, cut-up chicken in water and a little salt.
When cool, remove from bones.
Place chicken in loaf pan.

title: day before breakfast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Saute sausage.
Drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Layer the bread cubes, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour egg on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit cake surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put fruit in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Put box of cake mix on top of fruit.
Cut the butter into pats and place evenly on top of cake mix.
Bake for 45 minutes or until brown.
Let it cool in refrigerator.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix in soup and pizza sauce. Place on hamburger buns and top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes.

title: janice's sauerkraut casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Heat fruit juice to boiling; pour over the gelatin.
Stir well until dissolved.
Add Coca-Cola or 7-Up.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Break up or beat cream cheese and add to fruits and nuts.
Fold into gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Amounts of pineapple, cherries, cream cheese and nuts may be varied.

title: ice water pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions, peppers, garlic and salt in ice water for 3 hours, then drain off water.
Mix together sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed and place first mixture in this mixture.
Cook until cucumbers change color.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour and moisten with milk.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in egg yolks.
Add other ingredients and mix until dough is soft and very smooth.
To form cookies, pinch off small piece of dough.
Roll into ball size of marble.
Place on cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Press down with tines of fork.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°.

title: working mom's chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Lightly salt and pepper.
In a glass baking dish, pour enough crumbs to cover bottom.
Place chicken on top.
Pour crumbs on top of chicken.
Squeeze lemon juice on top.
Place butter in pats.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Best served with Rice-A-Roni (chicken flavor).

title: spicy golden pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into one greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or three greased 5 1/2 x 3-inch mini loaf pans.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes for a 9 x 5-inch loaf or 30 to 35 minutes for mini loaves, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely; store in the refrigerator.
The bread tastes great served either cold or warm with butter, cream cheese or jelly spread on top.
It also freezes well.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers or bread of your choice. It is great served with pita bread.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add flour and stir.
Quickly pour in milk and whisk until smooth.
Keep stirring until thickened and serve immediately.

title: lentil soup
directions: Place lentils and 4 cups of water in 3 quart casserole. Bring to a boil in microwave. Cook two additional minutes.
Let stand covered for 1 hour.
Pour 4 cups water, carrots, potato, onion, celery, and salt into lentil casserole.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes.
Stir casserole, then add sausage.
Cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are barely tender.
Remove and cool sausage. Melt oleo.
Blend in flour stirring gradually into soup until smooth. Skin, then slice sausages.
Mix into soup mixture.

title: hearty bean stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot with sandwiches and salad.

title: grandma's baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking
powder
and
salt.
Cut
in Crisco until fine.	Add egg to
which
has been added the milk. Toss ingredients lightly with
fork
(until
just moist).
Turn onto floured board and knead 5
to 6 times.
Flatten with hands to about 3/4 to 1-inch thickness
and cut with cutter dipped in flour.
Prick tops with fork and
top
with butter, milk or egg yolk.
Bake on greased sheet
for
approximately
15 minutes at 400° (preheated oven).

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat in eggs (and 1/4 teaspoon mint).
Stir in 1/3 cup light brown sugar, 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup cocoa.
Spread into pan.
Bake 23 to 25 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve soda and cream of tartar in milk.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add to milk mixture.
Sift about 4 cups of flour and start working this into the wet mixture. Use only enough flour to make soft dough.
Refrigerate dough overnight.
Roll out very thin and cut into cookies.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Watch carefully.

title: five-cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients all together, tossing lightly.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add eggs (no need to beat first), milk, canned pineapple, then bread cubes.
Blend together. Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes until top is brown.

title: blender pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in the blender until blended.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done. Yield:
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: mashed baked potatoes
directions: Boil
and
mash
potatoes.
In a separate bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, garlic salt, pepper and butter.
Add mashed potatoes and spread into baking dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo; add soup and Cheez Whiz.
When cheese is melted, add rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Boil broccoli in a little water and drain.
Mix broccoli with other ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: holubtsi - stuffed cabbage
directions: Fry onions and mushrooms slightly; add onions, mushrooms, salt, pepper and dill to rice.
Steam cabbage. Cut thick part of cabbage leaf.
Place ball of rice mixture in cabbage leaf and roll as for a jelly roll, pushing ends with fingers.
Put in roaster. Cover with tomatoes (1 large can or 2 pounds fresh tomatoes, strained).
Add 1 cup water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine beef, soy sauce, onion, eggs, parsley, garlic, cornflake crumbs, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape into balls the size of large olives.
Place in large baking dish.
Meatballs can be frozen at this point, if desired.
Combine cranberry sauce, ketchup, brown sugar, chili sauce and lemon juice in saucepan; heat, stirring well.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In shallow dish, dip chicken into egg; coat with bread crumbs. In skillet over medium-low heat in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides and no longer pink. Remove; keep warm.
Pour off fat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping and pour into crust.
Refrigerate

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast biscotti
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly oil and flour large baking sheet. Whisk together flour, corn meal, sugar, lemon zest, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, whisk together 1/2 cup water, eggs and vanilla; stir into dry mixture and stir in nuts and raisins. Divide dough into 3 equal parts.
On heavily floured surface, shape each portion into log about 13-inches long by 2-inches wide.
Place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Slice on diagonal into 1/2-inch slices.
Place on baking sheet and bake 15 minutes until very dry.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition. Add potatoes. Put in sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in 2 or 3 layers at 300° until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake before pouring over salad.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup well in microwave-safe dish.
Cook on High for 3 minutes and 30 seconds.
Carefully stir, then cook 2 more minutes.
Take out and add vanilla, butter and peanuts.
Cook 2 minutes.
Take out and add baking soda; stir well.
Pour onto a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Let cool.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: kid's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Dip pretty bottomed glass into water and press cookies down.
Sprinkle half with sugar and other half with cinnamon sugar combination.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix cocoa and water by adding water, a little at a time, until mixed well.
Cook until mixture gets thick.
Stir.
Take off heat.
Stir in corn syrup and mix well.
Put back on stove and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off and add vanilla.
Store in container.
Will keep in refrigerator.
Great over ice cream!

title: cracker snacks
directions: Stir together all ingredients and let set for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add 1 egg at a time, then the cream.
Blend well, then add vanilla and almond. Mix 3 tablespoons flour, salt and grated lemon peel; add to creamed mixture.
Pour into graham cracker lined pan (spring-form).
Bake in a 500° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 200° and bake for 70 to 75 minutes.
Test with silver knife; should come out fairly clean.
Refrigerate.
When cool, top with a can of pie filling or fresh fruit.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water about 30 minutes or until tender; chill.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Combine cheese, milk and 2 tablespoons butter in a small saucepan; cook over low heat until butter and cheese melt, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream, onion salt and pepper.
Fold cheese mixture into potatoes.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole; dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ham-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: canadian hamburger pie
directions: Fit one-half of unbaked pie crust into 9-inch pie pan.
Cook beef and onion in skillet until meat is brown.
Add marjoram, steak sauce, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, bouillon and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Turn into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Top with other pie crust, crimp edges and cut air holes in top.
Place pie in large baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients together.
Mix well, then add rest of ingredients.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes or until well blended.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: jellied seafood salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add cold water.
Put in refrigerator tray.
Let set until firm on edge.
Put in large bowl; whip until fluffy.
Add seafood, celery, olives and onion. Set until firm in a mold.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit; add water if necessary to make 2 cups. Heat juice to boiling; add gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Cool; add cola and fruit. Pour in mold. Chill until set. Serve with whipped cream or cream cheese.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box and let cool. Prepare Jell-O (do not use quick set directions) according to directions on box.
With fork, make rows of holes in cake, about 1 inch apart.
Spoon Jell-O over holes; don't be afraid to use too much, it takes quite a few spoonfuls to make the Jell-O soak all the way down the holes.
It won't be soggy after it chills.
You may have some Jell-O left over.
Chill cake.
Mix Dream Whip and spread over cake.
Serve chilled.
Great for summer!

title: ricotta cheese cookies
directions: Blend butter and ricotta cheese until it becomes creamy.
Add vanilla, and mix well.
Add sugar while gradually beating until well blended.
Add egg, and mix well.
Slowly stir in all dry ingredients mixing well.
Drop by teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 30 - 36 cookies.

title: fajitas
directions: Slightly brown chicken chunks on medium heat.
Add vertically sliced onion and green pepper.
Add sugar, basil, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook until done (approximately 5 minutes).
Heat tortillas in microwave until warm.
Serve fajitas mixture on tortillas.
Add tomatoes, cheese, salsa and sour cream.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Spread in bottom of 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Add rhubarb.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon together.
Add cream and stir well.
Pour over rhubarb. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge layer cake
directions: Cake: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter and flour two 9-inch cake pans. In large bowl, combine flour, sugars, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt. At medium speed, beat in milk, oil, eggs and vanilla until blended, about 2 minutes. At low speed, gradually beat in boiling water just until blended. Divide batter between cake pans. Bake 25 to 28 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pans on racks 15 minutes. Remove from pans. Cool on racks.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: Mix peppers, garlic salt and tomatoes in blender.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer about 30 minutes.
Put in jars, cool and refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well and pour in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: strawberry-almond parfait
directions: In a bowl, prepare pudding mix with milk as package directs, mixing in the almond extract.
Cover and refrigerate.
Sweeten strawberries with sugar.
Spoon about 3 tablespoons into each of six 8 to 10-ounce stemmed glasses.
Layer each with 3 tablespoons of cookie crumbs and 1/3 cup of pudding.
Top with the remaining strawberries and crumbs, dividing equally.
Garnish with mint sprigs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with a mixer.
Pour into two lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes and then top with glaze.
Loaves should sit in pans for several hours or overnight before being removed from their pans.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat in skillet first, then add all ingredients and simmer together for at least 1 hour.

title: lobster pie
directions: Add 1 cup of butter to the bread crumbs.
Add all ingredients and pour 2 cups of milk over contents.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1/2 or 3/4 hour.
Let it bubble.
If you like it soft, cover; if you like it crusty, do not cover.

title: cajun blackened fish
directions: Spread melted margarine over fillets.
Combine all spices and mix well.
Rub spices into fish.
Heat cast-iron skillet until very hot; watch carefully.
Cook fillets for about 3 minutes on each side, depending on thickness.
(Caution:
Cook outside or in very well ventilated area.)

title: chocolate pies
directions: Combine and cook over low heat until thick.
Add butter.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: smoked chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate 4 or 5 chicken breasts for 1 hour.
Prepare grill for direct heat cooking.
Place chicken breast on cooking grill.
Turn chicken every 10 or 15 minutes, basting with sauce each time.
Takes about 1 hour.

title: bug eyes
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, vanilla, crumbs and peanut butter. If mixture is too soft, more graham crumbs may be added.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax. Dip the balls in melted chips and wax with toothpicks; place on wax paper to dry.

title: pumpkin casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and
pour over margarine.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon on top of casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Total baking time 60 minutes.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Cook sugar, pineapple, cherries, flour and a little cake coloring until thick.
Add vanilla and orange jello and let cool. Add nuts and bananas and pour into pie shells.
Top with Pet topping or Cool Whip.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix condensed milk, butter, sugar, coconut and pecans together.
(Mixture will be very stiff.)
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Shape into balls (spoon size).

title: peachy bran coffee cake
directions: Drain peaches.
Reserve syrup.
Combine bran and 1/2 cup peach syrup.
Let stand.
Add egg, honey and margarine.
Beat well.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to other mixture.
Pour batter into oiled 9-inch square pan.
Make grooves diagonally in batter with floured spoon.
Place peaches in grooves.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Add tomato juice, water, rice and seasonings.
Put into a covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine all the ingredients and bake covered at 350° until all liquid is absorbed. Stir well before serving.

title: puff pastry
directions: Place Crisco and boiling water on burner until Crisco dissolves completely.
Add flour and salt to Crisco and water and stir until it forms a ball.
Remove from burner.
Add eggs, one at a time and stir until smooth.
Grease cookie sheet and drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Wet hands and make tips (like Hershey's Kiss.)
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake 10 minutes or more (oven temperatures may vary) until golden brown.
Using pastry bag, fill with chicken salad or other filling or you can lift top gently with a fork and fill.

title: crazy cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mixture is real thin.

title: turkey crescents(leftover turkey special)
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add milk.
Stir in turkey and pepper.
Separate dinner rolls.
Roll out.
Spoon in mixture into center of dinner rolls.
Wrap rolls up and seal. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until golden, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix
thoroughly all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake
about 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.	Pie is done when top begins to turn golden.

title: collards
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook until tender and most of water has cooked away.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute onion in 1 or 2 tablespoons oil until golden.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper. Brown and drain.
Alternate the hamburger, green beans and tomato soup in layers and top with mashed potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or use crock-pot.

title: kettle corn
directions: All ingredients are place in a crock pot and cooked on low or medium for several hours until hot and cheese is melted.

title: scalloped pineapple casserole
directions: Cream together eggs, butter and sugar.
Add crushed pineapple and place mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: magnificent mushroom spread
directions: In large skillet, saute mushrooms in butter 3 to 5 minutes. Combine onion, mayonnaise, bacon, salt and mushrooms.
Spread into a flat oven-proof dish.
(I use an oval dish 8 1/2 x 11 x 2-inch.) Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. (Be careful, it will be hot!)
Spread on cocktail rye rounds or crackers.
This may be assembled up to 2 days ahead.

title: cool-a-chino
directions: Place milk and cappuccino in blender.
Cover.
Blend on high until cappuccino is dissolved.
Add Cool Whip and cover.
Blend until smooth.
Serve at once.
Serves 1.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together crumbs, peanut butter, butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Mix well and form balls, 1 to 1 1/2-inches in size will do just fine.
Set aside.

title: sausage and cheese appetizers
directions: In large bowl, combine cheese, butter, flour, salt and pepper. Beat with mixer on medium-low speed.
Stir in sausage.
Form dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: tuna cheddar salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine tuna, apple, cheese and celery; toss.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir with a fork until well-blended.
Cover.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and cocoa together 3 times to mix well. Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored, then add milk and butter. Add alternately with dry ingredients to eggs. Makes 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes and almonds.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Add seasoned mayonnaise to chicken mixture and chill for several hours.
Serve on a lettuce leaf and top with pineapple chunks. Serves:

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: super brunch casserole
directions: Prepare the ingredients in an oblong 7 1/2 x 12 x 2-inch deep glass dish.
It must be made the day before serving.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped pecans and bananas. Spoon batter into either an 11 x 14-inch pan or 3 (9-inch) cake pans that have been well greased and floured.
Bake at 350° (25 to 30 minutes for round layers and 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan).
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely. Spread Cream Cheese Frosting generously over cake.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, mix eggs, add all remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch square baking pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
To brown top, put under preheated broiler for the last 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool a few minutes then cut into squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion until crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scandinavian spritz cookies
directions: Mix well and put through a cookie press.
Bake in a moderate oven until lightly browned.

title: marble squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease oblong pan.
Mix butter, sugars and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Blend in flour, soda and salt. Spread in prepared pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over top of dough.
Place in oven 1 minute.
Remove from oven and run knife through dough to marbleize.
Return to oven until golden brown. If using a large pan, double the recipe.
Marble Squares turn out better.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Let set in pan before serving.

title: christmas morn breakfast
directions: Make night before.
Place crescent rolls at bottom of square baking dish.
Cover with hash browns and sausage.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle fresh Parmesan cheese over top.
Refrigerate overnight if desired.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: celery soup
directions: Chop chicken, carrots and celery.
Wait until water boils.
Put in chicken, carrots and celery.
Put in sugar and salt.
Add the eggs and stir in flour.
Throw in macaroni.
Cook from 15 to 20 minutes.
Add black pepper when finished.

title: bird seed pine cones
directions: Spread peanut butter on pine cones and roll in bird seed. Attach a ribbon to the pine cone and hang from a tree.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well; shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Baste with sauce frequently.

title: baked fruit ambrosia(an outstanding compliment to serve with ham)
directions: Place in a 2-quart casserole in order listed with pie filling on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.
Do not cover casserole.

title: peggy's lemon pie
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Add Cool Whip; blend well.
Add vanilla and lemon juice last and, when mixture is smooth, pour into pie shells and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit salad with cream dressing
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water; cook, stirring constantly, 10 to 12 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from boiling water; cool.
Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form; fold into cooled mixture.
Serve immediately, or cover and chill for up to 3 hours.
Combine fruit, and serve with dressing.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: man's yeast rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix water and yeast, dissolve, set aside.
Mix flour, oil, sugar and egg.
Pour in yeast.
Mix well. Mix to biscuit consistency.
Make into balls (quarter size).
Put three balls each in greased muffin pans.
Bake 20 minutes.
Butter generously.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Cook and debone whole chicken, cutting into small pieces.
Cook egg noodles according to package.
Mix together chicken, noodles, soup, pimentos and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with salad and dinner rolls.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream together the
first 3 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients, adding the oatmeal last. Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: sherman's favorite green vegetable salad
directions: Put the last 5 ingredients in pan.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature before pouring on vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before using.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Marinate in the refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 13-inch baking dish and spread the pineapple over the bottom.
Spread the coconut and nuts over this. Distribute the dry cake mix over all evenly.
Slice 2 sticks of butter over this and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Salt and pepper.
Cook macaroni. Combine hamburger, macaroni and tomato juice.

title: grandma's stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bread, soak and squeeze out water. Place in a bowl; add 1/2 can tomato sauce, grated cheese, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stuff peppers; place on a slightly oiled pan.
Cook about 45 minutes or until tender with a fork.
Spoon on remaining tomato sauce; cook for a few more minutes.
Serve with soup and salad.
Super meal!

title: coffee punch
directions: Make coffee and cocoa the day before and let sit in refrigerator overnight. Whip cream; add sugar and vanilla. Put coffee and cocoa in punch bowl. Slice ice cream and put in punch. Add whipped cream.

title: tuna casserole(diet)
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: a b c chicken salad
directions: Thoroughly grill or broil chicken breasts and cut in diagonal strips.
Peel and slice each avocado into 8 pieces.
Peel bananas and slice them julienne-style.
Dip in pineapple juice to prevent discoloring.
Drain.

title: cream and candy cake
directions: Early in day, prepare cake mix as labeled. Cool.
Remove from pan.
Coarsely chop candy bars, set aside, with mixer at medium speed.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Slice or coarsely chop large pieces of cauliflower and broccoli.
In a large bowl, combine cauliflower, broccoli and onion.
In another bowl, beat together the Green Goddess dressing, salad dressing, vinegar and celery seed.
Pour over vegetables, tossing to coat well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Top salad with radish slices or cherry tomatoes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix until all are blended.
Add coconut.
Cook until thickened.
Pour in cooked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until fluffy; I add some sugar to mine to make stiffer.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown in oven.

title: renett's crisp cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add the rest of the ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into small balls and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 325° to 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese; add zucchini mixture.
Press refrigerated rolls into ungreased 10-inch pie pan to form crust. Spread crust with mustard.
Pour zucchini mixture into prepared crust.
Bake for 18 to 22 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: slush
directions: Mix in order and freeze.
Serve 2/3 slush and one-third 7-Up or Squirt.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook and stir onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in broth, chilies, salt, pepper, zucchini and corn.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Heat just until hot (do not boil).
Add cheese; sprinkle with nutmeg and parsley. Serves 5.

title: oobleck
directions: You will need a garbage bag to cover table.

title: cherry pie
directions: Put cherry pie filling in pie crust, put Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Unroll dried beef and place each chicken breast on 1 piece of beef.
Wrap bacon around each breast.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Spread over chicken.
Cover.
Bake 3 hours at 275° (for 2 hours at 300°).

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix drink mix, sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice, chill. Pour over sherbert and ice in punch bowl.
Add chilled ginger ale. Makes 50 servings.

title: lemon new potatoes
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat to 375°.
Lightly oil large, shallow baking dish.
Add potatoes to dish.
Mix lemon juice, oregano, lemon peel, salt and pepper in bowl.
Whisk in oil. Pour over potatoes; toss well.
Bake until potatoes are golden brown and knife pierces center easily, turning every 10 minutes, for about 1 hour.
Adjust seasoning.

title: ouzo cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle nuts evenly over bottom of pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil and ouzo.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour batter over nuts in tube pan; bake 1 hour.
Place on rack; cool 30 minutes. Invert on serving plate.
Prick with skewer and pour on syrup.
Let stand at least 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Mix bananas well or mash them.	Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool in pan for at least 15 minutes.
Cool on rack and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Can be baked in 13 x 9 for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: apple crumb
directions: Put apples, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in saucepan.
Cook and stir until apples are softened; set aside.
In mixing bowl, cream margarine and brown sugar.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pat 1/2 of flour mixture in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread apples over top.
Crumble remaining flour mixture over apples.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Serves approximately 14 to 16 (recipe can be halved).

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Put the cold (boiled, peeled, cubed) potatoes into a large bowl.
Pour melted butter over potatoes, stir well without tearing up the potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste, stir.
Add cheese, stir lightly.

title: clam linguini(high fat but low cholesterol)
directions: Into a pot place 2 cans of clams with juice.
Add to that 5 tablespoons of olive oil.
While heating on low heat, add 2 tablespoons of oregano, 1 teaspoon of Italian seasoning and garlic to taste (I like a lot!!).
Add one pinch of ground red pepper.

title: tasty onion rings
directions: Preheat deep fryer to 375°.
Mix two parts flour to one part beer in medium mixing bowl.
Stir with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Gradually add more flour and more beer until mixture is of a smooth texture.
If more flour is needed, gradually add small amounts until mixture is smooth but not runny.
Let mixture sit for three hours (at room temperature).

title: fresh orange salad
directions: Mix and set aside for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheddar ball
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving 1 tablespoon juice.
Beat together the cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and pineapple juice. Add pineapple, bacon, onion, soy sauce and salt; mix well.
Chill several hours, or until firm.
Shape to form 1 large ball or 2 small balls.*
Chill.

title: carrot shreds in bourbon and brown sugar
directions: Blanch carrots in salted boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain well and set aside.
Remove from water and rinse in cold water.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook
broccoli	according to package directions; drain. Stir in	remaining
ingredients	except	crumbs;
blend well. Turn into
greased,
shallow
2-quart
baking
dish; top with crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Then add milk.
Stir until well mixed.
Add bread and raisins.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Drain and when cool enough to touch, cut in bite size pieces.
In 2-quart casserole, blend chicken pieces and remaining ingredients, except potato chips and paprika.
Microwave (High), covered, for 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with potato chips and paprika.
Microwave (High), uncovered, for 5 to 7 minutes.
Rest 5 minutes.
Crisp top under broiler, if desired.
Serve with crackers or on toast.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put
layers of asparagus in bottom of greased casserole dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over asparagus; sprinkle cheese over crackers.
Continue until all asparagus is used.
Mix 1/2 can asparagus water to mushroom soup; pour over asparagus. Top with crackers and cheese.
Bake at 350° to 375° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bridal cake recipe
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Poke holes in cooled cake.
Pour entire contents of pineapple on top.
Blend cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread over pineapple on cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and churn.

title: helen's liver dumplings
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in pot with water, salt and pepper; cook until tender.
Remove meat.
Remove ligaments, etc. from liver; chop finely but do not grind.
Mix dry ingredients with liver and enough beef broth to make a soft dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling broth.
Cover and cook slowly for about 30 minutes.

title: ooey gooey bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix egg and cake mix. Press into pan.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lynn's chicken mornay
directions: Cover the bottom of a glass Pyrex baking dish with bacon.
Top bacon with broccoli spears and dollop with margarine.
Top broccoli with 4 or 5 chicken breasts and finish with another layer of bacon. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
